{"pages":{"page":[{"#text":"115 114 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Which brings us to one of Lamborghini’s main selling points – apart, of course, from the sheer beauty of the cars themselves. “Our customers can create the car that they want,” Wong says. “Thanks to our personalization program, we can basically do anything they can think of and that really broadens our customer base. “We had one guy with an iPad cover in matte purple and he loved the shade so much that we sent the cover to the factory so they could personalize the paint to the same color for his Huracán. “There was another lady who wanted her calipers in leopard skin. “We can even do the same for the interiors, such as how we stitch the leather of the seats. We had one customer with his name stitched into one side and the girlfriend’s name on the other side. The factory came back and said, ‘What happens if they break up?’ but that was okay. I told them, ‘He can just give her the car and come back to buy a new one for himself!’” 除了車本身的純粹魅力，林寶基尼其實還有別的主要 賣點。 黃卓徽表示，「顧客可隨心所欲打造自己的座駕。我 們的私人訂製服務，基本上可以滿足任何要求。這絕對拓 寬了我們的客戶群。」 「有一位客戶非常喜歡自己iPad外殼的顏色，啞光 紫。我們將外殼寄至工廠，為他的Huracán定制個性化油 漆。另外還有一位女士想將卡鉗塗成豹紋。」 「我們甚至可以有訂製內飾，比如怎樣縫製皮革座 椅。有一位客戶想把他的名字縫在一邊，女友的名字縫在 另一邊。工廠回來問我，如果兩人分手了怎麼辦？不過這 也不是問題，我告訴他們，他可以把這台車送給她，然後 為自己買台新車！」","@ID":58},{"#text":"9 8 SOUTH CHINA ELITE From the editor 編者寄語 Welcome to the first ever issue of South China Elite. We’re absolutely delighted to have you as a reader and hope you enjoy SCE for many years to come. South China Elite will showcase fascinating and extraordinary personalities from across the Greater Bay area – from Hong Kong to Shenzhen to Guangzhou to Macau – and elsewhere in Guangdong Province and South China. We’ll feature people mainly from the world of business, but we’ll also showcase academics, entertainers and others making a valuable contribution in developing the economy in this region which is amongst the fastest growing in the world. I had the privilege of being in Beijing this March during the liang hui – the annual plenary sessions of the National People’s Congress and the Chinese People’s Political Consultative Conference. It was there that Chinese Premier Li Keqiang renewed the push for greater integration and the Guangdong-Hong KongMacau Greater Bay Area concept. There is no doubt the 21st century will be the “Asian century”, fuelled in a major way by South China. Guangdong Province, Hong Kong, Macau and even the exciting Hengqin project personally supported by President Xi Jinping have crucial roles to play in this global shift. We are indeed privileged to have Senior Fellow of the Wharton School, Professor Dr Brian To grace the cover of our maiden issue. Despite holding no less than six post-graduate degrees fromsuch luminary institutions as Harvard and Oxford, Professor To is no “theoretical academic”. As a practice professor he travels the globe consulting to major Asian governments, militaries and corporations, coaching CEOs and global leaders and creating real economic value. As well as our cover story each issue focusing on one particular personality making a major contribution to the region, South China Elite will also have entertaining and informative articles contributed by some of the most eminent experts in the region, in our Business, Insights and Lifestyle sections. We hope these inform your business decisions and in turn grow your own personal wealth! Our company, O MEDIA, is no stranger to publishing. We currently publish Inside Asian Gaming, WGM andHigh Life, which first hit the streets in 2005, 2009 and 2016 respectively – and we have more digital and print media offerings planned for launch over the next 18 months or so. As a wise man once said, Learn from the Elite! Andrew W Scott Editor-in-Chief , May 2017 歡迎閱讀SCE創刊號。對於閣下成為SCE讀 者，我們深感榮幸，亦希望閣下往後繼 續閱讀SCE。 SCE為讀者們呈獻粵港澳大灣區出類拔萃的人事 物，當中有來自香港、深圳、廣州、澳門的，也有 來自整個廣東省及南華地區各地方的。我們採訪的 對象主要來自商界，但亦有在這全球其中一個經濟 增長最快的地區內，作出寶貴貢獻的學術界人士、 藝人，以及其他業界人士。 本年三月，本人有幸參與在北京舉行的全國人 民代表大會會議和中國人民政治協商會議全國委員 會會議。兩會上，總理李克強表示國家將加強推動 粵港澳大灣區整合發展的概念。 在南華地區的推動下，21世紀將毫無疑問成為 「亞洲的世紀」。廣東省、香港、澳門，甚至主席 習近平親自支持的橫琴項目，都會在全球經濟重心 轉移的過程中，扮演舉足輕重的角色。 SCE很榮幸邀得賓夕凡尼亞大學禾頓商學院資深研 究員Brian To教授，成為我們的創刊號封面人物。雖然 Brian To教授擁有多於六個由哈佛及牛津等著名大學頒 授的研究生學位，但是他絕非一名「理論派學者」。 作為實踐型教授，他足跡遍布世界各地，為亞洲多國 政府、軍隊及企業提供策略性建議，亦指導多位首席 執行官及全球領導人，從而創造確實的經濟價值。 除了專訪於本地區貢獻良多的封面人物外，SCE 還邀得區內最卓越的專家，在商業、見解及生活等 欄目撰寫文章。我們希望籍著SCE的專題，為閣下帶 來有助作出商業決定的重要資訊，並從而增加個人 財富！ SCE的母公司澳傳媒，在傳媒及出版方面擁有豐富 經驗，出版刊物包括分別於2005、2009及2016年創立 的《Inside Asian Gaming》、《環球博彩》及《品》 等。在未來18個月內，我們將會推出更多數碼媒體及 印刷產品。 一如智者所言︰向精英學習﹗ 卓奕 2017年5月 BEN BLASCHKE 本思齊 Managing Editor執行編輯 ANDREW SCOTT 卓奕 Editor-in-Chief 主編 EVELYN CHAN陳廸汶 Chief Content Officer編輯總監 RAQUEL DIAS戴樂瑩 Deputy Editor副編輯 SOPHIE HU户媛媛 Chinese Editor and Chief Translator中文編輯及主編 SANDRA NORTE Graphic Designer平面設計師 Editorial Team編輯團隊 PHOTOGRAPHERS 攝影師 ASSISTANT TRANSLATORS 助理翻譯 WILSON LI 李維遜 EDUARDO MARTINS DAPHNE HONG洪毅瑩 LEANNE LU陸逸","@ID":5},{"#text":"73 72 SOUTH CHINA ELITE The aforementioned countercyclical strategies are based on an assumption that business executives know when the peak will be and can therefore take action in advance. But how do you know the timing of these peaks? It is unrealistic for business executives to predict the exact date of a peak or a trough. However, statistics on the duration of previous cycles may provide some clues. The National Bureau of Economic Research (NBER), a well-known economic research institute in the US, offers just these statistics. NBER has a Business Cycle Dating Committee to determine business cycles in the US.  In 2010 the committee confirmed June 2009 as the trough of the economic downturn following the crisis of 2008 by considering a number of economic indicators. NBER has also identified all economic peaks and troughs in the US since 1857.  The following table shows those peaks and troughs after 1950 (the post-war period). Predicting turning points of an economic cycle 預測經濟週期轉折點 上述逆週期策略建基於這樣一個假設：企業管理人知道 高峰何時出現，因此可提前採取行動。然而，如何能知道高 峰的時機呢？要企業管理人準確預測高峰或低谷的確切日 期，無疑是癡人說夢。然而，過往經濟週期的長短，可能會 提供一些線索。享負盛名的美國全國經濟研究所，正為我們 提供了這些統計數據。美國全國經濟研究所設有商業週期定 期委員會，專責分析美國的商業週期。2010年時，委員會考 慮過一些列經濟指標後，確認2009年6月乃2008年金融危機 後的低谷。它亦列出美國自1857年起的所有經濟高峰和低 谷。以下列表列舉出1950年（戰後時期）的高峰和低谷。 TABLE表2 DURATION OF ECONOMIC PEAKS AND TROUGHS (SINCE 1950) 經濟高峰和低谷至持續時間 (自1950年起) Peak month 高峰月份 JULY 1953 1953年7月 AUGUST 1957 1957年8月 APRIL 1960 1960年4月 DECEMBER 1969 1969年12月 NOVEMBER 1973 1973年11月 JANUARY 1980 1980年1月 JULY 1981 1981年7月 JULY 1990 1990年7月 MARCH 2001 2001年3月 DECEMBER 2007 2007年12月 Trough month 低谷月份 MAY 1954 1954年5月 APRIL 1958 1958年4月 FEBRUARY 1961 1961年2月 NOVEMBER 1970 1970年11月 MARCH 1975 1975年3月 JULY 1980 1980年7月 NOVEMBER 1982 1982年11月 MARCH 1991 1991年3月 NOVEMBER 2001 2001年11月 JUNE 2009 2009年6月 Duration, peak to trough 持續時間 (從高峰至低谷) 10 8 10 11 16 6 16 8 8 18 Duration, trough to peak 持續時間 (從低谷至高峰) 45 39 24 106 36 58 12 92 120 73 Duration, peak to peak 持續時間 (從高峰至高峰) 56 49 32 116 47 74 18 108 128 81 Duration, trough to trough 持續時間 (從低谷至低谷) 55 47 34 117 52 64 28 100 128 91 Data source:  NBER (http://conference.nber.org/cycles/March91.html) NB: the “Duration” measured by month tells the length of economic cycles. 資料來源：美國全國經濟研究所(http://conference.nber.org/cycles/March91.html) 註：以月為單位的「持續時間」顯示經濟週期的長短","@ID":37},{"#text":"3 2 SOUTH CHINA ELITE • 1 2 | 3","@ID":2},{"#text":"83 82 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Since 2003, Hong Kong residential prices have been on an uptrend. It has registered stronger growth at +10.5% compound annual growth rate (CAGR) in the last decade (2006 to 2016) versus the previous decade (1996 to 2006) of -3.7%. It has beaten the inflation rate of +3.2% CAGR and the Hang Seng Index of +1.0% consistently. Apart from low interest rates (close to zero Fed rate) since 2009, a favorable undersupplied market and robust domestic/investment demand have been the key reasons. From a demographic perspective, new immigrants, non-local students, graduates and employees have been driving the demand for private residential units. In 2015, more than 56,000 people obtained work-related visas. About 30% of the 45,000 Chinese immigrants in 2016 had “one-way permits” to stay in private units. Meanwhile, 15,000 non-local students (the highest ever) enrolled in university programs in 2015/16. Many of these received permanent residency (PR) status after being in Hong Kong for seven years, including their university stay, and do not have to pay additional stamp duty for purchasing a residential unit. Abundant liquidity and high local investment demand are other driving forces. Investors accounted for 40% of private residential sales in 2011. This ratio reduced to 30% in 2016 after introduction of double stamp duty and buyers stamp duty, and further reduced to around 10% of sales volume after the government raised the double stamp duty rate again in November 2016. Despite the decline in the number of foreigners buying units, we see local home buyers use the loophole to purchase multiple units using single sale and purchase agreements to avoid heavy stamp duty. Hong Kong remains an aspirational place to own property for mainland Chinese. Hong Kong has been experiencing a shortage of private housing in the past 10 years or so, especially as the number of persons per household is decreasing. Private residential stock has grown at a CAGR of +0.8% in last decade, quite similar to population growth at +0.7% per annum but much lower than +1.1% domestic household growth. Despite the government increasing land supply in the last four years, completions lagged but now the supply of completed units is expected to reach 17,000 to 18,000 in 2017, much higher than the average of 12,000 in the last five years. 自2003年起，香港樓價一直節節向上。在2006年至2016 年期間，香港樓價取得了+10.5%的複合年均增長率，遠高於 1996年至2006年的-3.7%，亦一直高於+3.2%的通貨膨脹複合 年均增長率，以及+1%的恆生指數增長。除了自2009年起的 低利率（接近美國聯邦儲備銀行的零利率）外，供應不足及 需求強勁的本地/投資市場乃關鍵因素。 從人口學角度出發，新移民及非本地學生、畢業生及僱 員等，均是私人住宅需求的動力。2015年，逾56,000人獲發 工作簽證。45,000名中國大陸新移民中，約30%獲發單程證 並居於私人住宅。與此同時，15,000名非本地學生——此乃 歷來最高數字——於2015/16學年在香港各大專院校就讀； 其中不少人在香港居住滿7年後——包括其學生年代——已 獲發香港永久居民身份，故無需因購買住宅單位支付額外印 花稅。 資金充足及本地投資需求龐大，亦是主要的驅動因 素。2011年，私人住宅交易中40%屬投資性質。香港政府實 施雙重印花稅及買家印花稅後，比例稍微回落至2016年的 30%；香港政府於2016年11月提高雙重印花稅後，比例進一 步下跌至10%。儘管外地買家購買私人住宅的數字有所下 降，但本地買家為避免印花稅，利用漏洞以單一合同形式購 買多個住宅單位。對中國大陸居民而言，香港仍然是購買房 地產的理想之地。 過去10年，香港一直面臨私人房屋短缺的問題，每戶人 數正在減少是其中一個成因。過去10年，私人住宅庫存錄得 +0.8%的複合年均增長率，與每年+0.7%的人口增長率相若， 卻遠低於+1.1%的本地家庭增長率。儘管政府在過去4年增加 土地供應量，但住宅單位的建成速度卻相對慢；不過，新建 成住宅單位數量在2017年將上升至17,000至18,000個，遠高 於過去5年的每年平均12,000個。 從人口學角度出 發，新移民及非 本地學生、畢業 生及僱員等，都 是私人住宅需求 的動力。","@ID":42},{"#text":"53 52 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Israel has about 90 NASDAQ listed companies, Hong Kong 20-plus. Why the difference? Let me answer this in three parts. Security of mind. Firstly, you have to understand the Hong Kong model. Most people in Hong Kong came from South China, particularly from Guangdong. Some swam across. My dad, for example, came as a refugee as didmany others. It was not an unusual story in the late 1940s and ‘50s – with political and social problems on the mainland it was the so-called, “I’ve-got-to-get-out-of-here” mentality. So people came and they were on their guard. There was only one university and you had to be top 1% to get in. It was very much, “You’d better study hard – and don’t forget your uncles and aunties.” It was all about collaboration but it was also about security of mind, which demands conformism. The older generation would say, “Don’t think like that. We are in the grocery business, or the hotel business – that’s what we know.” That kind of culture doesn’t really foster innovation, because there’s you and there were these Hongs. So the professionals gravitated towards the Hongs but the rest followed Mom and Pops and these family owned boutique enterprises, which have done remarkably well over the years. There’s no place I can think of that replicates these circumstances except countries in Southeast Asia. Security was of paramount importance in those times. Conservatism. When you look at the numbers, about 93% of businesses are family owned enterprises, meaning owned, controlled or managed by families in Southeast Asia outside of Japan. That means many companies of all shapes and sizes are patriarchal in nature and style. The boss in some instances comes into the office on Fridays and signs a few cheques, says a few words, then heads off to the golf course. It reminds me of an experience with a main board public listed company. They invited me to sit on their corporate listed board. They said, “Oh Brian, you’ve got a little bit of education, you look Chinese and you should sit on our board, say a few words and take us out of the ice age.” So I said, “Okay, let’s engage all of the board members.” It took about a week to interview separately each board director and appreciate them individually. After these interviews I was quite chuffed and thought, “Onto the next phase.” But then after the interviews they said, “What are you doing Sunday? You must come for Dim Sum!” On that Sunday it was the matriarch of the company who sat at the head of the table. Among the questions she asked me were, “What year were you born? What time were you born? What is your Chinese Zodiac? Where did you get those ears?” without a single question about my education or professional experience. But she was the one who scrutinized all senior decisions about new board members. Finally, I was made to understand that she made the final decision. Granny evidently was not even mentioned in the annual report, but she was the one who actually makes the decision. Welcome to Asia! International demand. The fragility of Hong Kong was exemplified by SARS. Never have I seen fear like the fear I witnessed among residents at this time, unless you were to go back to the Japanese invasion or something similar. If you coughed on a bus or a train you would immediately have a free seat beside you. There was deep paranoia at that time as Hong Kong citizens rushed to Australia and Canada and other places. During the SARS epidemic, hotels were made to innovate to drive and sustain business. Now you had five buffets a day in hotels instead of three. Companies and people, by necessity, took initiative to innovate. But Hong Kong is still the gateway to China, even if Shanghai is coming up fast. So, if you wanted law and order, transparency and a legal system that protects, all these companies who want to come in, where do you go? There are only a few choices: Singapore or Hong Kong. Here in Hong Kong, we understand western culture is not new. You can get every kind of food and every kind of product and professional service, and where it matters everyone speaks English. 以色列約有90家企業在納斯達克上市，而香 港僅有20多家。這是為甚麼？ 讓我以三部分回答這問題。 第一是安全感。首先，我們須了解香港的模式。很多 香港人祖籍華南地區，尤其是廣東，其中不少人當年是涉 水渡河到香港的，家父即為當年眾多難民中的其中一名。 由於中國大陸當時的政治及社會動盪——這在上世紀四五 十年代很普遍，人們懷著破釜沉舟的心態來到香港，所以 警惕心甚強。那時候，香港只有一所大學，能夠進入大學 的，無不是名列前茅的精英。 那時候的想法是︰「最好努力學習，且不要忘記還在 中國大陸的親戚」。這是關乎合作和安全感的問題，故要 求人們順從。老一輩總是說：「別作他想，我們經營的雜 貨業或旅館業務，正是我們所能理解的。」 這樣的文化，是無助促進創新的。年輕專業人士要麼 加入大集團工作，要麼繼承父母衣缽經營小型家族企業； 話說回來，這些小型家族企業多年來表現出色。類似香港 這種環境，似乎只有東南亞地區。在動盪時期及過後，安 全感總是最重要的考量因素。 第二是保守主義。統計數字顯示，東南亞地區（不包 括日本）的企業中，有高達93%是家族企業，即企業有家 族成員控制、掌管及管理。這意味著不少大小家族企業， 都以家長式方法管理。不少老闆僅於週五踏進辦公室，簽 了幾張支票、說了幾句話後，便離開辦公室前往爾夫球場 了。這讓我回想起與某家上市公司的經歷；當時，這家上 市公司曾邀請我加入其董事局。 他們對我說：「你讀過不少書，看上去又像華人。你 應該加入我們的董事局，說幾句話就可以引領我們走出冰 河時代。」 我回答說：「好的，先讓我與所有董事局成員接觸 吧。」如是這，我花了一個星期，逐一會見及了解董事局 成員。會面過後，我滿心興奮的想：「我準備好下一個階 段了。」 然而，他們過後問我：「週日你有甚麼節目嗎？跟我 們一起到茶樓飲茶吧！」週日飲茶時，坐在主席位置的是 企業老闆的母親。她問了我不少問題，其中包括「你是在 哪裡出生的？」、「在甚麼時辰出生？」、「你的生肖是 甚麼？」、「你的耳朵怎麼會這樣的呢？」云云，就是沒 有一個問題跟我的專業經驗有關。這位老太太，是垂簾聽 政審視董事局每一個重要決定的人。最後，我明白了—— 她是真正掌控權力的人。這位老太太的名字，沒有出現在 年度報告中，卻是最終決策者。這就是亞洲！ 第三是需要。香港的脆弱，在非典型肺炎事件中表露 無遺。我從來沒看見過這樣的恐慌，是瀰漫在居民之間的 一種恐慌；對上一次出現這樣的恐慌，可能要追溯至日本 侵華時期了。如果你在巴士或列車上咳嗽，身邊的乘客肯 定馬上遠離你。當時介乎歇斯底里的恐慌，導致不少香港 居民跑到澳洲及加拿大等地。非典型肺炎肆虐時，酒店被 迫創新以繼續生存——房客在酒店裡可享用5頓而不是3頓 自助餐。時世所迫，企業及個人要繼續生存，就須創新。 儘管上海迅速冒起，但香港仍然是通往中國的門戶。 如果你要的是法治、秩序、透明度，以及保護企業的法律 制度，那只有兩個選擇——新加坡及香港。在香港，我們 對西方文化並不陌生；在那裡，你可以找到各類食品、產 品及專業服務，而且所有人基本上都會說英語。","@ID":27},{"#text":"69 68 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 大多數企業管理者均意識到經濟週期，希望以低 廉的價格購買資產，並在低谷過後不久以較低 的價格擴展業務。與此同時，他們均希望在經 濟週期的高峰時出售其資產、業務或股票。可惜，他們總是 因錯失最佳時機而感到遺憾。股市崩潰時，他們知道經濟衰 退已無可扭轉；資產價格上升時，他們卻認為擴展業務成本 高昂。 本文旨在討論如何以更佳的企業策略應對經濟週期，亦 列出有助企業管理者乃至專業經濟師，預測未來高峰和低谷 的各項指標。 Most business executives are aware of riding an economic cycle. They wish to buy assets at low prices and expand their business at cheaper costs shortly after a trough.  Meanwhile, they all wish to sell their assets, their business and their shares at the peak of a cycle. Unfortunately these business executives are always disappointed at missing the best timings. When the stock market crashes, they realize recession is already there. When asset prices rise, they find it costly to expand their business. This article aims to discuss some better corporate strategies to deal with economic cycles. It also identifies indicators that help business executives to mirror professional economists in predicting upcoming peaks and troughs.","@ID":35},{"#text":"116 SOUTH CHINA ELITE","@ID":59},{"#text":"113 112 SOUTH CHINA ELITE “We’re definitely trying to push it higher,” he says. “I mean, we’ve got a lot of successful females, women who are very strong and have very strong careers. At the same time our cars have become more accessible. “Our newest cars like we have now, the V10 and V12 derivative, both have semi-automatic gear boxes – they are not manual – and there are different modes that we can set to change the dynamics of the car. Both cars have three modes – the Strada (street), Sport and Corsa (race course) – so when you put it into Strada you essentially have a fully automatic car where the damper is softened, the steering becomes light, it’s easier to park and the engine is softer so you can listen to music. “We are also doing lots of test drives now so even when a male comes in to look at the car and they are going to do a test drive, I always ask them to bring their wife ... because the wife is the decision maker of the household! I ask them to take a drive and once they get into the car it’s actually quite easy. The visibility is great and also, in a Lamborghini you definitely get respect on the road. When you change lanes, people let you pass. They want to look at the car and they also don’t want to scratch you up! So they are great on the road and yes, we have seen lots of women coming into the Lamborghini family.” 他說︰「我們正著力推動這個市場。如今有不少成功 女性，而我們的車型亦較以往更加容易操作。像我們最新 車型V10和V12的兩條動力線都是非手動的，而是備有半自 動變速箱；另外，我們還有其它可調節的模式，可供我們 改變車的動力。兩條動力線都提供Strada公路、Sport運動 和Corsa賽道三種駕駛模式。當你調到Strada模式，基本就 是一輛全自動車，減震變軟，方向盤變輕，易泊車，同時 引擎聲變小，可以聽音樂。」 「我們還做過很多試駕。男士來看車並且想試駕時， 我總會請他們帶上太太，因為太太是掌握大權的人！我會 請他們試駕，一旦進了車裡，事情就變得容易了。品牌辨 識度很高，在路上必定讓你備受禮遇——變道時，其它車 都會禮讓；他們想端詳一番，當然也不想刮擦到你的車！ 駕駛林寶基尼上路絕對是很棒的體驗。我們確實看到越來 越多女性加入到林寶基尼大家庭。」","@ID":57},{"#text":"45 44 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Why this new and emerging interest in ethical leadership? This is how I look at it. As we are intently watching the global markets, both Fortune 500 and Inc 500 companies continue to look at China and India as the key major mega markets where opportunities for market expansion are vibrantly increasing in different corners. On the other hand, Chinese businesses are also eyeing more aggressively companies overseas in North America and Europe. Looking back, while hospitality is still a key component of doing business in Asia, the historical way of doing business has changed from the past where companies relied heavily upon relationships (Guanxi) and facilitation where budgets appear to be modest. Moving forward, the focus has shifted to more stern corporate transparency requirements, dual listings, more special audits and independent overseers – thus stirring up a sharp demand for more ethical leadership not only in China but also in the global business environment. With recent notable leadership practice challenges in Malaysia, the Philippines, South Korea, Brazil and Taiwan, it’s becoming more evident that both country and corporate leadership must become more principled and ethical if business sustainability and change are to be achieved.  The recent cases of Volkswagen and Mitsubishi erring in corporate and consumer disclosures clearly reveals that the challenge has pervaded not only in China but in the global arena as well. How will these affect management education? Foremost, let’s understand that China has made education a national priority. Almost every week a new university opens its doors in China. Equally sobering and compelling is that at least 40% of the world’s engineering and technical graduates are minted each year in China and by 2020 it is expected to be around 60%. The implication of such significant upsurge of graduates is so compelling given the fact that the number of patents filed each year on the mainland has On ethical leadership 論合乎道德倫理的領導管理 been growing dramatically over the last eight years. More than ever, Management and Business degree programs must be relevant and practical, since the library of congress now almost doubles itself every four years. Towards that end, it’s even more important that graduate business education must be taught by leading practitioners together with experienced faculty. In recent years, many EMBA programs have come under heavy criticism as many participants have been enrolling for the purpose of networking and for future access. Needless to say, this is unfair, if not awkward. This motive has not considered the many benefits participants may have enjoyed and that they may have eventually applied whatever significant learning they would gain in building business development initiatives and facilitating business from Hong Kong to Shanghai to Singapore along with many other key cities in the region. Thus, that leading EMBA and DBA programs need to be responsive to market needs and conditions has become more of a compelling necessity than a mere option in management education. As the demands grow, emerging special programs such as Conflict Management, Business and Behaviour, Global Trends and Social Network Theory will definitely emerge. As such, learning for all of us has no other option than to be perpetual and lifelong. Leadership education obviously is not effective if attended once every 20 years. Study of leadership should not be restricted to a discussion about the latest fads and models but must go deeper into the anatomy of leadership coupled with a profound understanding of Behavioural Science. All too often, leaders today are promoted within corporations not because of their innovative or motivational abilities and skills but because of their politically savvy and manoeuvring. To answer the question, these last few years the impact on teaching has in fact been dramatic with more than 50,000 published theories released. In the present teaching erawhere competition is getting tougher every day and there are unavoidable economic changes, education is imperative. Moreover, what strikes the balance between chaos and functioning is leadership. 人們為何會對合乎道德倫理的領導管理這新 思維感興趣？ 我的個人看法是，我們關注全球市場發展的同時，財 富500強及Inc 500強企業均視中國和印度兩大市場為商務擴 展的重點，並大力在各領域進行投資。另一方面，中國企 業亦更積極地瞄準並投資北美及歐洲等地的企業。 雖然人脈仍是在亞洲營商的重要元素，但企業過往以 關係為主導的方式——那是從前預算額有限的年代——已 經起了變化。展望將來，重點將轉移至更嚴格的企業透明 度要求、兩地上市、專業審計和獨立監督等，意味在中國 乃至全球商業生態中，合乎道德倫理的領導管理將逐漸變 成常態。 馬來西亞、菲律賓、南韓、巴西及台灣最近均出現針 對政治領導人的挑戰。這證明要實現企業可持續發展和變 革，國家及企業領導管理均須朝著合乎道德倫理的方向發 展。大眾和三菱等企業最近備受醜聞困擾，顯示問題不僅 存在於中國，亦存在於全球其他地區。 這對管理教育將構成甚麼影響？ 首先，我們要知道，中國將教育視為國策的重中之重。 中國幾乎每個星期就迎來一所新的大學，而同樣引人注目的 是，全球至少40%的工程及技術系畢業生，都是中國培育的； 到了2020年，比例將進一步上升至近60%。畢業生人數激增的 同時，最近8年間在中國提交的專利申請數目亦大幅上升。 現時，國會圖書館的藏書數量，每隔4年就翻倍，而商業 管理等課程的相關性與實際性，就更是必須。更重要的是，學 位後商業管理課程須由有經驗的實踐型專家任教。近年來，不 少高級工商管理碩士課程因淪為學員擴展網絡的台階，而飽受 批評。這無疑是不公平的，也是令人尷尬的——這是忽略了 學員獲得的不少益處。學員最終可能會學以致用，在香港、上 海、新加坡乃至本地區其他主要城市促進商務發展。 因此，頂尖的高級工商管理碩士課程及工商管理博士課 程，需迎合市場環境及需要。對管理教育而言，這並不是選 擇，而是有迫切的需要。隨著需求增長，衝突管理、商業與行 為、全球趨勢及社會網絡理論等新興專業課程將應運而生。對 所有人而言，這意味著除終身學習外，並無其它選擇。","@ID":23},{"#text":"21 20 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Most corporations neglect the missing piece in the middle. When formulating strategy, there is an impatience in executing that strategy without first developing it. When you jump from formulation to execution you neglect the key fact which is that it should go from formulation to development – then execution. Development is an important detail because this is where innovation takes place. Companies that try to jump this stage don’t benefit from innovative processes. Too often it is a rehash of what has been done before so they don’t benefit from the presence of new ideas, new initiatives and thinking differently about markets. This has to be appreciated because research into product cycles shows them to be increasingly rapid. Previously, product cycles would run two or three years. Now they run two or three months. So engaging themarket with themand getting feedback is necessary. The research suggests that of all the new products going into the market each year, more than 68% of them will be taken off the market within 18 months. 大多數企業的致命傷，是忽略了中間的關鍵部分。制 定策略時，企業往往急於實施策略，卻沒有發展策略。從 制定策略直接跳到執行策略，就忽略了發展策略這一關鍵 階段。發展策略的重要性，在於這正是實行創新的階段。 如企業忽略了發展策略這階段，則無法享受創新過程中獲 得的成果。若企業只重新調整從前的計劃，便無法以新思 維、新計劃及角度審視市場。 這是極為重要的，因為研究顯示，產品週期正變得愈 來愈急速。從前，產品週期可持續兩三年，現在是兩三個 月。因此，與市場接軌並獲得回饋是有必要的。 研究亦顯示，每年進入市場的新產品中，有68%以上的 產品在18個月就黯然離場。","@ID":11},{"#text":"23 22 SOUTH CHINA ELITE BB: You’re a change agent then? BT: In every situation and instance you’re a facilitator of change as an advisor or professor. Yes, I believe all of us are fundamentally change agents, albeit often we are reluctant to change ourselves. BB: Finally Brian, what led you in this career direction? BT: It’s merely the fulfilment of a childhood dream. I used to listen to my father and the meetings that he had. I was only four or five years of age and I always wanted to be able to contribute to business and always wanted to be a business consultant. But I was ambitious as a child. I always wanted to be a professor too. I wanted to pass knowledge onto others. And I also wanted to be in the military! I had aspirations for all of those things. Today I am involved with the military, with non-profits, I’m heavily involved in academia as well as advising CEOs and board members. 本思齊：你是帶動變革者嗎？ Brian To博士：身為顧問或教授的人，在任何情況下均是 協助變革的因素。我認為我們本質上都是促進變革的因素，儘 管我們往往不願意改變自己。 本思齊：最後，驅使你選擇這個事業的原因為何？ Brian To博士：我只是在實現自己的童年夢想。小時候， 我常聽家父說他參與過的會議。那時候，我年僅四五歲，卻一 直想為企業作貢獻，並成為商業顧問。我也雄心勃勃要成為教 授，將知識傳給別人。同時，我又想加入軍隊！小時候，我懷 有多個理想。今天，我如願以償地參與軍事、非牟利組織及學 術界等項目，並為首席執行官和董事局成員擔任顧問。","@ID":12},{"#text":"37 36 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Over the next 10 years, Frank Knight projected that a surge of 71% of billionaires in Asia would attain almost the same number as in the US. The billionaires in China and India are projected to increase by 75% and 105% respectively over the next decade. As individual wealth continues to multiply at such an awesome scale, the need for private banking and wealth management business is indisputable. The critical success factors are to develop strategies and modus operandi that are befitting to the banks’ own strengths and weaknesses, are cost effective and sustainable. The good old days of doing private banking and wealth management business has gone with the wind. The rapidly changing environment and market place demand that banks and their senior management adapt to the new paradigms. Any banks and financial institutions still clinging to their old-fashioned ways will become relics. 萊坊預計在未來10年，亞洲的億萬富翁人數將激增71%， 幾乎與美國看齊。同時，中國和印度的億萬富翁，人數將分 別激增75%及105%。 鑑於個人財富幅度增長持續驚人，私人銀行和財富管理 的需求是必然的。 提供這些服務的機構的成功關鍵因素，在於發展出合 適的特性、能揚長避短、具成本效益與可持續性的策略及運 作模式。私人銀行和財富管理從前的好時光，已經一去不復 返。 瞬息萬變的環境和市場，令銀行及其高級管理層不得不 去適應新模式。任何固步自封的銀行和金融機構，必將成為 歷史。","@ID":19},{"#text":"63 62 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Going back to our current view on the market, we would highlight the following. MSCI China is trading at around a 5% valuation premium to EM, on 1.6x trailing price/book value, and yet with ROE at 12% is delivering a 20% ROE premium. We have similar forecasts for China and EM of low teens earnings growth in 2017, in both cases coming off two bad years for earnings, but our higher forecast return for China comes from our expectation of relative multiple expansion, from around parity now to a 10% premium by the end of the year. The catalyst for this re-rating is not, we suspect, any rapid reversal of foreign investors’ underweight stance on China, though we think that will reduce, but much increased Southbound Connect flows from the Chinese mainland into Hong Kong. These flows are increasingly institutional in nature and are taking advantage of discounted H share valuations relative to A shares for dual-listed names. Quality Hong Kong-listed names such as Tencent, ChinaMobile andAIA, which are not listed onshore, also offer diversification benefits for domestic investors. These southbound flows are running at close to US$1 billion per week in the year to date and we expect around US$30 billion to US$50 billion cumulatively for this year in total. 我們對當前市場的看法，可總結為以下要點。MSCI中國 指數的交易估值溢價，比MSCI新興國家指數高出5%，即歷史 本益比/賬面價值的1.6倍，但股本回報率卻高達12%，帶來 20%的股本回報率溢價。由於中國與新興國家均經歷了兩年 的收入不景氣，我們預計兩者在2017年錄得低於15%的收入增 長。然而，我們針對中國的最高回報預測，來自我們對多重 擴張的預期，即介乎現水平與年底的10%溢價。我們估計，導 致上述重新評估的主因，並不是外國投資者突然間扭轉對中 國股票市場投資不足的局面——儘管我們相信這局面將會改 變——而是由於從北至南的港股通流量大增。這些流動愈加 以機構為主，並利用股票雙重上市的H股對A股貼現估值。沒 有在中國境內上市的騰訊、中國移動和AIA等，均是在香港上 市的優質股票，亦為國內投資者提供多元化的收益。最近一 年，港股通每週總值已接近10億美元。到年底，我們預期全 年累計總值將介乎300億美元至500億美元。","@ID":32},{"#text":"33 32 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 成功的關鍵因素 管理高淨值人士財富的金融機構，有不少種類。在香港 和新加坡，主要有銀行、證券公司、獨立財務顧問、資產管 理及基金公司、家族辦公室，以及私募股權公司等。這些機 構均受新加坡金融管理局、香港金融管理局，或香港證券及 期貨事務監察委員會監管。 在亞洲，銀行依然是管理多數高淨值人士資產的機構。 以2016年為例，瑞士銀行管理約2,740億美元的資產，緊隨 其後的是花旗銀行和瑞士信貸。在全球，瑞士銀行管理的資 產總值約為1萬億美元。在亞洲，規模排名首20位的銀行， 管理的資產總值約為14,700億美元。其它非銀行金融機構所 管理的資產總值相對微不足道。資產和基金管理公司主要管 理銀行（由高淨值人士投資）、本地以及國際機構投資者的 投資基金。獨立財務顧問及家族辦公室等，則管理其它零星 資產。 私人銀行和財富管理業務能否成功、獲利及持續發展的 關鍵因素，在於他們能否以最理想的成本收入比例，吸引及 保持高淨值人士的財富。 Critical Success Factors There are various types of financial institutions handling the wealth of the HNWIs (High Net Worth Individuals). In Hong Kong and Singapore, these consist mainly of the banks, securities houses, independent financial advisors (IFAs), asset management and fund companies, family offices and some private equity firms. All these companies are regulated by either MAS (Monetary Authority of Singapore), HKMA (Hong Kong Monetary Authority) or SFC (Securities and Futures Commission) in Hong Kong. In Asia, the banks still hold the largest amount of AUM of the HNWIs. UBS, for example, had about US$274 billion of AUM in 2016; followed by Citibank and Credit Suisse (globally, UBS maintains the biggest AUM of about US$1 trillion). Total AUM of the largest 20 banks amounted to about US$1.47 trillion in Asia. The other non-bank financial institutions retain inconsequential assets. Asset and fund management companies hold investment funds mainly from banks (invested by HNWIs), domestic and global institutional investors. IFAs and family offices hold other scattered assets. The critical determinant factors for a successful, profitable and sustainable private banking and wealth management business are the financial institution’s ability to attract and maintain the wealth of the HNWIs, at an optimal cost-to-income ratio. Outsiders are now imposing how the insiders should do their jobs. 現在，外行人指 示內行人該如何 行事。","@ID":17},{"#text":"105 104 SOUTH CHINA ELITE","@ID":53},{"#text":"97 96 SOUTH CHINA ELITE “We have something for everyone” Ewa explains with visible excitement. “We cover all the different market segments, from speedboats to luxurious, tailormade yachts. Beneteau, one of the brands we represent, has motorboats that would be perfect for a beginner or someone who doesn’t want to spend too much money. On the other end of the spectrum is Sanlorenzo, a brand known for its super yachts.” Indeed, Simpson Marine’s portfolio includes an impressive list of eight brands represented in China, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Taiwan and Thailand. They include Montecarlo Yachts, Montecarlo, Viking, CNB, Beneteau Sailing Yachts and family friendly brand Lagoon Catamarans. Ewa 興奮之情溢於言表，「我們能滿足各種需求，涵蓋 所有不同的細分市場，從快艇到豪華訂製遊艇。博納多是我 們旗下的代理品牌之一，他們的摩托艇對初學者或不想太過 破費的顧客來說，是理想之選。而聖勞倫佐則是一個以超級 遊艇著稱的品牌。」 辛普森遊艇的產品目錄共有八個品牌，在中國、香港、 印度尼西亞、馬來西亞、新加坡、台灣和泰國市場推出，其 中包括蒙地卡羅遊艇、蒙地卡羅、Viking、CNB、博納多帆 船，以及適合家庭的品牌藍高。","@ID":49},{"#text":"57 56 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Insights 見解","@ID":29},{"#text":"13 12 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Ben Blaschke: First of all Brian, you are very much a modern globalist in that you consult to a number of large corporations from a range of sectors all around the world. Can you provide a bit more detail on your role? Dr BrianTo: As a strategist and a practice professor for more than 20 years I have the pleasure and privilege of working on complex situations in different sectors of industry, government and various leading institutions around the globe. I work in a number of countries and am privileged enough to consult and to teach a range of organizations where I focus largely on issues such as culture, diversity and the effects of culture and diversity on productivity. Working in several countries simultaneously for these past decades hasmademe evenmore appreciative and respectful of the importance of community, human dignity and human performance and the need for collaboration in all work – from assisting in developing national competitiveness models to developing global growth strategies for corporations. I’m grateful for the opportunity to be involved and to be able to bring the three key essential key drivers to all of the projects I work on – namely innovation, competitiveness and behavioural science. 本思齊：你為全球不同業界的大型企業擔任顧問，可謂 當代全球性策略家。可否解釋一下你扮演的角色？ Brian To博士：作為策略家及實踐型教授，我有幸在過 往20多年間，為全球各地的企業、政府以及頂尖機構處理各 種複雜的問題。我在不同的國家工作，並有幸在多間組織裡 擔任顧問及任教，其中以文化、多元性以及兩者對生產力的 影響等為重點主題。 對於有機會參與並將三大關鍵要素——即創新、競爭 力及行為科學——應用到我負責的項目，我感到十分榮幸。","@ID":7},{"#text":"71 70 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Corporate strategies and economic cycles An economic cycle is comprised of two major parts and four stages. Part 1 is “Peak to Trough”, including the stages of recession and depression.  In a recession period, both business activities and asset prices decrease. Banks become more conservative in lending.  In a depression period, people are very pessimistic about economic prospects. Many companies go bankrupt and the unemployment rate soars. Part 2 is “Trough to Peak”, including the stages of recovery and prosperity. In a recovery period, corporations begin to expand their businesses and the unemployment rate drops. In a prosperity period, corporate revenue increases and rental charge soars. In this period, inflation increases such that everything becomes more expensive.  Graph 1 summarizes these stages of an economic cycle. Most companies adopt procyclical strategies for business management. When economic environments are prosperous, they have cash inflows increased and thus expand their business aggressively. When the peak soon passes and recession arrives they face losses and close down some operations in the period of depression. Many over-expanded companies collapse in this period. In fact, these strategies passively react to economic cycles. Being a survivor in economic downturns is a necessary condition for a company to grow. To deal with recession and depression, companies need to think about countercyclical strategies. More specifically they must adopt countercyclical strategies in the prosperity period. These strategies include: 1. Getting sufficient long-term funds: During economic downturns, a company makes less, even negative profit, and finds it hard to get bank loans. All lenders are extremely conservative in economic downturns. If the company gets sufficient long-term funds from equity issuance, bond issuance or new loans in advance, the company will easily sail through those hard times.  It will even be capable of acquiring new assets and expanding its businesses when everything becomes cheaper. 2. Closing down less profitable operations: In the period of prosperity, the company can review the profitability of their business units and close down the unprofitable ones. This saves plenty of cash flow during economic downturns. 3. Tightening credit lines:  Many companies become insolvent because their debtors are unable to pay in economic downturns.  To avoid this, companies can review credit lines offered to their customers before economic downturns.  It can offer discounts for cash sales, especially to those less credible customers. THE STAGES OF A TYPICAL ECONOMIC CYCLE 典型經濟週期的各個階段 GRAPH圖1 Business Activities Trough Trough Prosperity Recovery Prosperity Peak Recession Depression Years 經濟週期由兩大部分及4個階段組成。第1部分是「高峰至 低谷」，包括衰退和蕭條階段。在衰退階段，商業活動及資產 價格均下跌，銀行在貸款方面變得更保守。在蕭條階段，人們 對經濟前景非常悲觀，不少企業破產，導致失業率上升。 第2部分是「低谷至高峰」，包括復蘇及繁榮階段。在復 蘇階段，企業開始擴展業務，失業率隨之下降。在繁榮階段， 企業收入上升，而租金則激增。此時，通貨膨脹導致所有商品 服務變得昂貴。圖1總結了經濟週期的各個階段。 在商務管理領域，大多數企業採用順週期策略。經濟環境 大好時，它們的現金流入量增加，並積極擴大業務。高峰過後 衰退來臨時，它們即面臨損失，並在蕭條階段結束某些業務。 不少過度擴展的企業，就是都在這個階段倒閉。事實上，這些 策略均以被動的態度應對經濟週期。 能夠在經濟衰退時存活下來，是企業得以發展的必要條 件。為應對經濟衰退及蕭條，企業須考慮逆週期策略。具體而 言，它們須在繁榮階段採取逆週期策略，包括： 1. 取得足夠的長期資金：經濟衰退時，企業盈利會較低 甚至虧本，亦難以獲得銀行貸款。此時，所有貸款人會變得極 為保守。假若企業預先以發行股票、債券或新增貸款取得足夠 的長期資金，它們便可安然地度過艱難時期。所有商品服務變 得便宜時，它們甚至有能力收購新資產並擴展業務。 2. 結束盈利較低的業務：在繁榮階段，企業可審視各業 務部門的盈利水平，並結束盈利較低者。這有助企業在經濟衰 退時期，節省大量現金流。 3. 收緊信貸額度：企業陷入破產的原因，不少都是因為 其債務人未能在經濟衰退時償還債務。為避免這種情況出現， 企業可在經濟衰退前審視給予客戶的信貸額度，亦可針對不太 可靠的客戶提供現金折扣。 TABLE表1 PROCYCLICAL CORPORATE STRATEGIES V COUNTERCYCLICAL CORPORATE STRATEGIES 企業順週期策略對企業逆週期策略 Stage of an economic cycle 經濟週期階段 RECESSION 衰退 DEPRESSION 蕭條 RECOVERY 復蘇 PROSPERITY 繁榮 Procyclical strategies 順週期策略 Keep less profitable operations 保留盈利較低的業務 Close down unprofitable businesses Sell off businesses 結束盈利較低的業務 出售業務 Start to expand business 開始擴展業務 Expand business aggressively 積極擴展業務 Countercyclical strategies 逆週期策略 Acquire assets and expand business 收購資產並擴展業務 Close down less profitable operations Arrange long-term funds (equity, bonds, loans) Tighten credit lines 結束盈利較低的業務 準備長期資金（股票、債券及貸款） 收緊信貸額度 企業策略及經濟週期","@ID":36},{"#text":"29 28 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 二零零八年在美國觸發的次按危機，成為近年 全球（尤其是亞洲）私人銀行與財富管理歷 史的轉折點。 在銀行業中，2008年9月15日乃具有劃時代意義的日 子：那天，擁有158年歷史的雷曼兄弟申請破產保護。倒閉 前，雷曼兄弟是一家管理逾2,750億美元資產的投資銀行。 雷曼兄弟倒閉的影響力無遠弗屆，從華爾街蔓延至世界每 個角落，全球多個國家級及國際級金融中心，無一倖免。 不少金融機構及銀行，相繼陷入資金不足的致命困境。瑞 士銀行、德意志銀行、蘇格蘭皇家銀行及美林證券等全球 金融巨人，無不面臨破產，僅靠各國政府及中央銀行救市 才得以脫離困境。 自那天起，各國中央銀行及金融中心的監管機構，皆 收緊對銀行及金融機構活動的監管。 2008年及2009年，象徵私人銀行與財富管理業界開始 The watershed year of the current history of private banking and wealth management globally, particularly in Asia, was 2008 – the final blastoff of the Subprime Mortgage financial crisis. There was a very distinct demarcation of this industry on the fateful day of 15 September 2008, when Lehman Brothers filed for bankruptcy protection after being in operation for 158 years.  Before its collapse, the investment bank had in excess of US$275 billion in assets under management (AUM).  This debacle sent shockwaves from Wall Street to every corner of the world. Every domestic and international financial center was affected. Many mega financial institutions and banks literally got into liquidity quagmire. UBS, Deutsche Bank, Royal Bank of Scotland, Merrill Lynch and a list of colossal global banks plainly became “bankrupt”, only saved by their countries’ respective central banks or national governments. Since this day, all central banks and regulatory authorities of the international financial centers have tightened their grip on the activities of the banks and financial institutions. 2008 and 2009 were the inception of a new phase of the private banking and wealth management (PB/WM) industry. The pendulum has swung from the free-forall, laissez faire and create-anything-you-like investment habitat to a progressively vigilant predicament. Slowly and surely, the central banks and regulatory authorities of all the international financial centers have taken over the central stages to dictate how the private banking and wealth management professionals should play the game. This is the comical aftermath where outsiders are now imposing how the insiders should do their jobs. The avalanche of new guidelines, regulations, disciplinary punishments with huge fines and detailed instructions on how a bank and its relationship managers or client advisors (RMs or CAs) should handle clients escalated the costs and difficulties of managing the private banking and wealth management business. Internal compliance, risks and legal departments of the banks further exacerbated the situation by adding extra “juice” such as additional guidelines on how front-line staff should administer their marketing and investment activities. Clients were enraged over these extraneous procedures, documents and controls that needed to be executed before any investment transaction could be consummated. Everyone is a loser. 進入新時代。宏觀發展的趨勢，從極端自由放任主義走向 愈加嚴格的警惕監察。各國中央銀行及各大國際金融中心 的監管機構，均循序漸進地發揮其作用，規管私人銀行與 財富管理專業人士的行事模式。 環球金融危機帶來其中一個古怪的後遺症，是外行人 指示內行人該如何行事。 鋪天蓋地的新指引、法規、處分、巨額罰款，以及針 對銀行、其客戶經理及客戶顧問與客戶交涉的詳細指示， 都增加了私人銀行與財富管理業務的成本及管理難度。在 此基礎上，銀行的內部法規審查、風險及法律等部門，均 加入針對前線員工的營銷和投資活動指引，令情況雪上加 霜。 這些無關重要的程序、文件及控制等，必須在完成任 何投資交易前辦妥，讓客戶感到不勝其煩。在這樣的制度 下，所有人都是輸家。","@ID":15},{"#text":"93 92 SOUTH CHINA ELITE “He was sailing around the continent with his girlfriend and decided to build his own boat,” explains Marketing Manager Ewa Stachurska. “To his surprise, as soon as he reached Taiwan he was approached by a buyer, wishing to purchase it.” The story repeated itself twice before he realized he should turn his passion into a business – and that’s how the yacht sales and charter company was founded, focusing on meeting the needs of the developing marine industry in Asia. By the end of the 1980s, the company had been appointed as regional distributor for several leading European and Asian yacht brands. Hong Kong was first choice because the market was far more mature than in other destinations around the region. Today, the company has more than 20 offices in seven countries. 集團市場經理 Ewa Stachurska 解釋說︰「麥克和女友 環球航行期間，決定打造自己夢想中的遊艇。意外的是，抵 達台灣之後，立即有買家找他，希望購買他的遊艇。」 同樣的事發生兩次之後，他意識到可以將熱情與商機結 合起來。於是，一家遊艇銷售和租賃公司便應運而生，旨在 滿足亞洲市場的需求。到了1980年代後期，公司已經成為多 個歐洲及亞洲領先遊艇品牌的區域經銷商。香港是首選，因 為香港的市場比區內其它地方要成熟很多。如今，公司在七 個國家設有二十多個辦事處。","@ID":47},{"#text":"89 88 SOUTH CHINA ELITE When our Deputy Editor Raquel Dias is not writing or chasing stories for O MEDIA, she is usually reading, listening to rock & roll or coloring books. Raquel is a Mozambican-born Portuguese who has lived in Macau for most of her life. After studying History and Social Anthropology in the UK, she came back home with a newfound love for Macau. Having worked in media since she graduated, Raquel likes to think of herself as a storyteller rather than journalist. 為澳傳媒撰寫文章及安排採訪外，副總編輯戴樂 瑩酷愛閱讀、搖滾樂及為書本填色。戴樂瑩是在 莫桑比克出生的葡萄牙人，大部分時間在澳門居 住。於英國取得歷史及社會人類學學位後，她重 返澳門開展其事業。自大學畢業後一直在傳媒界 工作的戴樂瑩，視自己為說故事者多於記者。 Raquel Dias 戴樂瑩 Call of the sea 大海的呼喚 By Raquel Dias 文︰戴樂瑩 Hong Kong’s Simpson Marine has been providing luxury yachts to Asian seafarers for more than 30 years. 在三十餘年，香港辛普森遊艇（Simpson Marine）一直為亞洲出海愛好者供應豪 華遊艇。 About the author 作者簡介","@ID":45},{"#text":"81 80 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Shelter or a place to live is the most basic and physiological need for humans, according to Maslow’s hierarchy of needs. But in Hong Kong, this has been much more than that. Based on Forbes’ list of richest Asian families in 2016, three Hong Kong families were ranked among the top 10, all of whom have created their wealth primarily from property. For Hong Kongers, property ownership also provides safety (second level) and even esteem (fourth level of needs). In 2016, real estate, construction and ownership of premises accounted for 19.1% of Hong Kong’s real GDP, and contributed 0.35 percentage points to overall growth of 1.9%. 根據馬斯洛的需求層次理論，容身之所乃人類最 基本的生理需要。然而，香港的情況遠遠不止 於此。根據2016年度福布斯亞洲最富有家族排 名，名列首10位的香港3大家族，無一不從事房地產。對香 港人來說，擁有物業亦是對安全的需求（第2級），以及尊 重的需求（第4級）的泉源。 2016年，房地產、建築及物業擁有權合共佔香港本地生 產總值19.1%，亦佔1.9%總體增長中的0.35%。","@ID":41},{"#text":"25 24 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Business 商業","@ID":13},{"#text":"43 42 SOUTH CHINA ELITE What are your current thoughts about Hong Kong? The decision in Hong Kong to vote down the electoral reform package last year has caused Hong Kong residents to think seriously about the future of the territory. Perhaps this is an indication that the gap is closing between the mainland and Hong Kong despite a deadlock of political challenges. How have recent ties been between China, Hong Kong and Taiwan? Mounting challenges for China’s President Xi Jinping on the South China Seas and continued tension amid the economic slowdown has not deterred China from closing its political and cultural grip on both Hong Kong and Taiwan. Last March, this was confirmed at the China People’s Consultative Conference, one of the most senior political advisory bodies in the congress, and the National People’s Congress – despite the recent demands from seniors within Hong Kong for an increasing degree of economy and democracy. If applicable, this will mean China will be balancing one country, three systems if Taiwan fails to continue recognizing China’s 1992 consensus of One China. One can expect that Taiwan will drag its heels, whilst China may slow economic development and political communications with the new leadership of Taiwan. One may also presume that the mainland will tighten its grip on both Hong Kong and Taiwan this coming year. What should we be expecting from China in the future? China, I believe, will push forward towards closer cooperation with countries not only within ASEAN, but with the EU and almost all developing countries including Africa and America.  For example, bilateral annual trade volume with the EU is expected to reach US$1 trillion in a few years, but no later than 2020 which is a mutual goal. Despite a slowdown this year, it seems manageable if China maintains a 6% to 7% GDP year-on-year. The same opportunities also apply in both central and eastern Europe. The impact of the recent global financial crisis and the middle east migration of displaced refugees has created distractions but creates even more debt in the Eurozone, France, Greece, Spain and Turkey among others. These countries are being hit even more so with increasing labour strikes. Therefore Europe may delay China and the EU reaching its trade goals, particularly since the loss of labour overall has been rising in the EU for the last six years. Another indication of China’s rapidly rising role in global leadership is the AIIB (Asian Infrastructure Bank). Already half of all EU member states are founding members. Equally impressive is the recent agreement between the IMF and AIIB to consider joint process. Additional joint investment funds will follow to compliment the One Belt, One Road initiative which, with the Chinese mega project of infrastructure development, will certainly shroud the building of The Great Wall. Despite the global economic slowdown, China will continue to forge new partnerships and explore new opportunities regionally and globally. 你對香港當前的情況有何看法？ 香港立法會於2015年否決政改方案後，不少香港居民開 始認真地考慮特區的未來。儘管政治僵局持續，這或許證明 中港兩地之間的差距正在縮小。 中港台之間的關係最近有何發展？ 國家主席習近平因南海問題及經濟增長放緩而備受 壓力，卻無損中國逐步收緊對香港及台灣的政治和文化影 響。2016年3月，全國政協及全國人大無視香港民主派元老 要求更大的經濟及民主自主權，就確認了上述的決心。如台 灣不繼續承認1992年達成的一個中國共識，意味中國將以一 國三制作平衡。不難想像，台灣可能會採取不合作態度，而 中國則可能放慢就台經濟發展及政治問題與台灣領導人對話 的步伐，並進一步收緊對港台兩地的控制。 中國在未來將有何舉措？ 我相信中國將與東盟、歐盟乃至非洲及南美等大多數發 展中國家發展合作關係。例如，中歐的雙邊貿易額預計在未 來數年間將突破1萬億美元大關；於2020年前實現這目標， 是雙方的共同目標。 儘管經濟放緩，中國取得按年6%至7%的增長率，還屬控 制範圍之內。中歐及東歐多國亦擁有相同的機會。 全球金融危機的後遺影響以及中東戰亂導致的難民潮， 不僅對各國構成問題，更導致歐元區內法國、希臘、西班 牙，甚至歐元區外的土耳其等國債務惡化。愈加頻繁的工 潮，更令情況雪上加霜。因此，中歐之間要達致貿易目標， 可能需要更多時間，尤其是因為歐盟在過去6年間損失了不 少整體勞動力。 亞投行的成立，是中國在全球體系中領導能力提升的 又一標誌。歐盟各國中有近半是亞投行的創始成員，而國際 貨幣基金組織與亞投行最近達成協議考慮雙邊合作，更是令 人鼓舞。隨之而來的投資基金，可支持中國最近宣布的一帶 一路發展策略。中國投資的基建項目，其數目之多及規模之 巨，將可媲美長城。儘管全球經濟放緩，中國將繼續建立新 的合作夥伴關係，並在全球開拓新機遇。","@ID":22},{"#text":"51 50 SOUTH CHINA ELITE What about the ability to innovate in China? In fairness, innovation efforts in China in recent years have been breath taking with the growth in innovation labs and the encouragement by the Central Government for business enterprise to search for innovative solutions. It is clearly a cornerstone of the economy for business growth and development. What might help and accelerate this key functioning is the constant coaching of this process with profound understanding of the necessary culture in order to support innovation within any organization. For example, in Israel you see that companies are constantly coming up with novel products. It’s a 24-hour, 360-degree challenge and opportunity for the growing economy. And whether it is about developing security systems in Israel or games in Taiwan or new technologies On innovation 論創新 in the San Francisco Bay Area, we must be reminded that the choice is crystal clear: innovate or die. Simply stated, the challenge for China is its ability to innovate in this next decade as it is becoming more predictable as more and more Chinese Brands become household names. The thinking in Israel is entirely different. Their starting point is, “We are surrounded. We’ve got to innovate to survive.” Clearly it’s about courage, risk and taking initiative. You only have to look at how many Israeli companies are now listed on the NASDAQ exchange. But it all starts with leadership, the way management and decision-making takes place and the time it takes to get things done coupled with the additional time to market. The Israeli culture supports innovation, competitiveness and internal collaboration. Perhaps there is a lesson here for all of us to learn from? 中國創新能力如何？ 平心而言，中國的創新領域近年來取得驚人的發展，這 有賴中央政府鼓勵創新實驗室發展，為企業尋找創新方案， 亦顯然是經濟增長和發展的基石。在深入了解文化的基礎 上，籍著持續推動此過程支持不同組織內部的創新，將有助 加速創新這關鍵要素。 比如說，以色列的企業總是在推出新產品。對發展經 濟而言，這是全方位全天候的機會。無論是研發以色列的安 全系統、台灣的電子遊戲或三藩市灣區的新科技，我們均須 提醒自己眼前的選擇是極為明確的——要麽創新，要麽被淘 汰。 未來10年，隨著更多中國品牌成為家喻戶曉的名字，中 國的創新能力會變得愈來愈容易預測。簡而言之，中國所面 對的挑戰，在於其如何創新。 在這議題上，以色列的思維則完全不同。以色列的出發 點，是「我們被鄰國包圍，必須創新才能生存」。這顯然關 乎勇氣、風險及採取主動的問題——君不見以色列有多少企 業在美國納斯達克交易所上市？凡此種種，均源於領導管理 層面，即管理和決策的方式、完成項目所需的時間，以及營 銷產品所需的額外時間。以色列文化支持創新、競爭力和內 部合作。這對我們而言，豈不值得學習？ 這與香港的創新能力有何關係？ 在香港企業的任何部門，每天總有人說「我們只是微不 足道的小僱員而已」，或「我不能將自己的真實想法告訴大 老闆」云云。 在大多數情況下，創意靈感總是首先經過資深員工過 濾，再由傾向過度保護的行政人員審查，然後是高級行政人 員審視，最後才送達主管審閱。如果該主管與其它主管或秘 書的關係欠佳，創意靈感將到此為止。 以列車為例，所有車廂總是由最前方的機車拉動，這正 是香港的情況。以色列的模式，是讓個人擁有自己的機車， 然後匯集在一起。當然，任何組織均須設有正式和非正式的 架構，但在參與方面，以色列的模式鼓勵個人參與，從而在 個人層面轉化為文化及激情。因此，就成果而言，在政治框 架內運作的組織，總是不及以「成績」為主導的組織。 How does that relate to the ability to innovate in Hong Kong? In any sector in Hong Kong on any given day, one can hear people saying, “I am only a small potato” or, “I can’t tell Big Boss what I really think.” Typically, innovative ideas are going to be filtered by more senior staff, then reviewed by senior executives with unnecessary intervention by protective administrative staff. It then goes up for scrutiny by a Director and if the Director doesn’t have a good relationship with another Director or Secretary, then “POOF” – there goes your idea up in smoke. Take the example of a train. A single locomotive pulls an entire train of carriages and in Hong Kong they all follow behind one locomotive. In the Israeli model, everyone has their own locomotive and are all pulling together. Of course, in any organization there has to be formal and informal organizational structures, but in terms of involvement it becomes a culture and a passion at an individual level for all to be encouraged to participate. Hence, those organizations that operate mostly within a political frame obviously do not have the same results as those focused to operate in the “outcome” frame.","@ID":26},{"#text":"31 30 SOUTH CHINA ELITE The additional compliance costs, plus the requirements to strengthen internal IT capabilities to capture any undesirable activities of clients made the private banking and wealth management business for the smaller banks and units unprofitable.  “Red flags” and improved KYC (Know Your Customer) profiles added tremendous costs to the banks. Many banks found it futile to continuously appease the insatiable regulators. The prognosis by the author in his book Private Banking & Wealth Management in Asia – An Insider Perspective (2014, Warrior Books) that there would be only two categories of private banking and wealth management banks which would survive the current and future environment is unfolding. The private banking and wealth management businesses of Credit Agricole, ING, Societe Generale, Barclays, Coutts and ABN AMRO have been sold. A few more in the middletier will become antiquity in the near future. Eventually, the two types of private banking and 額外的法規審查成本，以及強化監察客戶不當行為的 內部科技所引致的支出，均令小型銀行以及部機構的私人銀 行與財富管理業務變得無利可圖。風險警示及「認識你的客 戶」資料系統，令銀行的成本激增，以至不少銀行認為，不 斷滿足監管機構日新月異的要求，實在徒勞無功。 筆者在《亞洲私人銀行與財富管理——內行人觀點》 （Private Banking & Wealth Management in Asia – An Insider Perspective）（2014年， Warrior Books出版）一 書中，預期只有兩類私人銀行與財富管理機構能在當前以及 未來的環境下生存。這預測正逐漸實現——法國農業信貸銀 行、ING集團、興業銀行、巴克萊銀行、Coutts銀行以及荷蘭 銀行的私人銀行與財富管理業務，均已被出售，而另外數個 中型銀行的相關部門，亦快將成為歷史。 wealthmanagement banks that can ride out the current storm are the mega global banks such as UBS, Credit Suisse, Citibank and JP Morgan; and the boutique or “pure-play” banks such as Pictet, LGT, EFG and Union Bancaire Privee. This scenario will prevail until the pendulum of regulatory bearings moves from extreme tightness to the pivotal center. But alas, the new CRS (Common Reporting System) signed by Hong Kong, Singapore, China and most Southeast Asian counties will come into effect in 2018.  This would cast the industry into another impasse, where all the banks and financial institutions are required to file client-sensitive data to the CRS. This database would be shared internationally to prevent money laundering activities and any undesirable movements of funds.  The final ramifications are still unknown. Is it worthwhile, then, to remain in the private banking and wealth management business or call it a day? Does the industry still have a future? 最後，兩類能安然渡過當前風暴的私人銀行與財富管 理機構，將是全球性大型銀行如瑞士銀行、瑞士信貸、花 旗銀行和摩根大通等，以及如Pictet、LGT、EFG及Union Bancaire Privée等小型精品或「單一業務」機構。 在監管的發展趨勢從矯枉過正回歸至正常力度前，此情 況將會持續。然而，香港、新加坡、中國以及大部分東南亞國 家簽署的全新共同申報準則（Common Reporting System），將 於2018年生效。根據系統要求，所有銀行及金融機構均須呈交 客戶的敏感資料。這將令業界陷入另一個僵局。此數據庫是國 際共享的，以防止洗黑錢活動及其它不當資金流動。其最終結 果為何，現在還不得而知。 那麼，我們是否還值得繼續私人銀行和財富管理的業 務？還是應該打退堂鼓？這個行業是否還有未來？","@ID":16},{"#text":"101 100 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Services are extensive with the company not limiting itself to just selling boats. They also provide assistance once the purchase is completed as well as ensuring one of their experts personally goes to the shipping yards to ensure maximum quality and client satisfaction. Ewa explains that China remains a relatively new market but perceptions are changing fast. “We’ve noticed a great difference in five years, the number of private owners is increasing,” she says. “We think the first step for this to happen is investing in Charter more. This way individuals can experience first-hand the joy of being close to the sea.” She adds that the high import tax in China, more than 40%, remains a barrier to the business. 公司服務範圍廣泛，除出售遊艇之外，亦提供廣泛的售 後服務，並會派送一位專家親自前往貨運場地，以確保最高 的品質和客戶滿意度。 Ewa解釋說，中國仍是一個相對較新的市場，但人們對 遊艇的認識正迅速轉變。 「我們留意到過去五年裡的巨大變化，私人擁有者的數 量持續增加。我們認為，第一步是在租賃業務上增加投資， 以令更多人可親身體驗親近大海的樂趣。」 她補充說，中國進口稅高達40%以上，仍是這項產業的 一個絆腳石。 VIKING","@ID":51},{"#text":"111 110 SOUTH CHINA ELITE While Hong Kong’s once revered luxury goods market has declined markedly in recent years, Wong says that Lamborghini has been somewhat shielded from its impact – a fact he attributes to the company’s unique standing as a global icon of achievement. “We tend to occupy the ultra-luxury market,” he explains. “For our client base the luxury car is actually a small part of their assets so it’s more on a sentiment basis. “With a strong brand like Lamborghini, it’s viewed as a benchmark for success so we have a strong following in Hong Kong and we’re targeting a bigger audience than emerging markets. “In China for instance, because we have a dealership there, most of our customers are entrepreneurs or owners of companies but here we actually see a lot of professionals becoming our customers, like lawyers, doctors, bankers – these guys are making the kind of dough to put them in that position. “These are guys that have their life in their own hands and they know what they are doing.” Lamborghini is also seeing renewed interest from female customers, who are increasingly attracted to the supercar market as a symbol of their own power and independence. Naturally, it’s a market Wong welcomes with open arms. 儘管香港曾經如日中天的奢侈品市場近年顯著下滑， 但黃卓徽表示，林寶堅尼並沒有受其影響。他認為這是由 於品牌在全球均被視為成功標誌的獨特地位使然。 他解釋說︰「我們傾向於佔領超級奢侈市場。對我們 的客戶群而言，豪華座駕只佔他們資產的一小部分，因此 他們多是出於情愫而購買。 「林寶堅尼這樣的優質品牌被視為成功的標誌，因此 在香港有不少追隨者，並且相對於新興市場，我們有更大 的目標客戶群。 「比如中國內地，我們在那裡有經銷商，客戶大多 是企業家或公司老闆。但在香港，很多專業人士如律師、 醫生和銀行家，亦是我們的客戶。這些客戶擁有足夠的財 力，並對自己的生活駕馭自如，知道自己在做什麼。」 林寶堅尼也越來越受女性客戶追捧，她們逐漸被超跑 市場所吸引，視之為權力和獨立的象徵。自然，這也是黃 卓徽非常歡迎的市場。","@ID":56},{"#text":"59 58 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Jonathan Garner is Morgan Stanley’s Chief Asia and Emerging Market Equity Strategist. He joined the Firm in 2006 having held similar positions at Robert Fleming, DLJ International and Credit Suisse from 1997. Earlier in his career, Jonathan worked as an academic in the economics department of the London School of Economics. He is the author of The Rise of the Chinese Consumer, published by John Wiley & Sons in 2005. Jonathan has been top-three ranked on a regular basis in buy-side surveys, such as Thomson Reuters Extel and Institutional Investor, in the emerging markets and Asia equity strategy categories. Jonathan Garner 現為摩根士丹利亞洲及新興市 場股票策略部主管。於2006年加入摩根士丹利 前，他曾任職於富林明集團、DLJ International 及瑞士信貸。Jonathan Garner 早年曾於倫敦 經濟學院經濟系任教，及後於2005年撰寫《中 國消費者的崛起》（John Wiley & Sons出版） 一書。在新興市場及亞洲股票策略買方研究範 疇，Jonathan Garner 一直被 Thomson Reuters Extel及Institutional Investor列入三甲排名。 Jonathan Garner Jonathan Garner, Managing Director and Head of Global Emerging Market Strategy at Morgan Stanley, outlines the financial services firm’s view that Chinese equities will continue to outperform those of emerging markets. 摩根士丹利亞洲及新興市場股票策 略部主管 Jonathan Garner，闡述 摩根士丹利認為中國股票市場表現 將持續領先於其他新興國家股票市 場之看法。 Why we are bullish on China 我們緣何看好中國 By Jonathan Garner 文︰Jonathan Garner About the author 作者簡介","@ID":30},{"#text":"65 64 SOUTH CHINA ELITE The broader context for mainland China equities is that investors are rotating away from bonds and property back towards stocks with an improving earnings growth outlook amidst higher inflation and demand-side property control measures. Meanwhile, the domestic regulator has followed through on its August 2015 plan to allow domestic pension funds to invest up to 30% of their net assets in equities (versus zero previously). Mandates were awarded last December by the National Pension Fund to 21 asset management companies to invest in equities and these funds have begun to be invested in the local equity market as of last month. In conclusion, the outlook for China equities is bullish from both a structural and cyclical perspective. We believe valuations are reasonable, earnings growth is recovering and long-term institutional capital is increasingly moving into the market. 受高通貨膨脹以及針對需求的房地產控制措施影響，中 國股票的大趨勢是投資者從債券和房地產領域，轉移至盈利 增長前景良好的股票。與此同時，國內監管機構亦按照2015 年8月制定的計劃，容許國內退休基金以其淨資產總值最高 30%的額度投資股票。此前，國內退休基金是不能投資股票 的。去年12月，中國全國社會保障基金批准21家資產管理公 司投資股票，而後者已於上月開始投資本地股票市場。 總而言之，無論以結構性和週期性的角度出發，中國股 票市場的前景均是良好的。我們認為估值處於合理水平，盈 利增長正在復蘇，更多機構長線資本正在進入市場。","@ID":33},{"#text":"27 26 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Private Banking & Wealth Management expert KC Tew examines the impact of the global financial crisis on the banking industry and whether the Private Banking & Wealth Management industry still has a bright future in Asia. 私人銀行與財富管理專家KC Tew， 深入分析全球金融危機對銀行業的 影響，以及私人銀行與財富管理在 亞洲的前景。 Mr KC Tew is an experienced professional in private banking, wealthmanagement and financial consulting. Over the past 30 years, his career span has covered banking and industrial areas in Singapore, Hong Kong, Taiwan and Shanghai. Mr Tew has an Honors degree in Physics, an MS in Management & Organizational Development and an MBA in Finance with a minor in International Business. He is currently pursuing a DBA degree. He is now a freelance financial consultant, advisor, speaker and trainer. His primary life goal is to share his experience with newcomers, senior professionals, management and anyone who is interested in the private banking and wealth management industry. 張金全在私人銀行、財富管理和財務顧問領域擁 有豐富經驗。過去30多年間，他曾在新加坡、香 港、台灣和上海等地的銀行及工商界任職。 張金全擁有物理榮譽學士、管理及組織發展碩士 以及工商管理碩士（副修國際商業）學位，現正 攻讀工商管理博士課程。張金全現為自僱財務顧 問、演講者及導師。他的人生目標為與一眾新進 及資深專業人士、高層管理人員，以及對私人銀 行與財富管理感興趣的人士分享其經驗。 KC Tew 張金全 About the author 作者簡介 Current trends of private banking and wealth management in Asia 亞洲私人銀行與財富管 理之近況及動態 By KC Tew 文︰張金全 b i andwealthmanag t exa ines the impact of the global fina cial crisis on the banking industrya whether theprivatebanking and wealth management industry still has a bright future in Asia. 張金全深 入分析全球金融危機對銀行業的影 響，以及私人銀行與財富管理在亞 洲的前景。","@ID":14},{"#text":"75 74 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 美國全國經濟研究所已確認上一個高峰及低谷分別是 2007年12月及2009年6月。根據表3統計總結，我們可以上一個 高峰及低谷、中位數、最高四分之一及最高值為基礎，預測 下一個高峰。 根據表4所列結果顯示，美國經濟顯然已通過「最高四分 之一」，並開始進入「最高值」。這意味著高峰即將來臨， 緊隨其後的是衰退。此時，企業管理應立即審視： (a) 這是否擴展業務的好時機？ (b) 企業應否收緊客戶的信貸額度？ (c) 假若供應商終止供應鏈信貸額度，企業能否繼續生存？ (d) 企業是否過分依賴銀行短期貸款？ (e) 企業是否擁有足夠的現金及流動資產應對經濟衰退？ (f) 企業應否準備更多長期資金？ 美國全國經濟研究所的經濟週期分析，主要聚焦於美 國。這個全球最大經濟體的繁榮及蕭條週期，會大大影響美 國入口及美國企業的全球策略。其它經濟體——尤其是以出 口為主的國家以及新興國家——將受到美國經濟蕭條影響。 NBER has confirmed the last peak as being December 2007 and the last trough as June 2009. With the summary statistics in Table 3, we can predict the next peak. Projections can be estimated with the last peak and trough plus medium, upper quartile and maximum. Table 4 shows the results. It is obvious that the US economy has just passed the dates of “Upper Quartile” and is moving towards the “Maximum”.   This means the peak will arrive soon and recession will follow. Business executives should immediately ask themselves: (a) Is it a good time to expand the business? (b) Should the firm scale down its credit lines offered on customers? (c) Will the firm be able to survive if suppliers stop their supply-chain credit? (d) Does the firm rely too heavily on short-term bank loans? (e) Does the firm have sufficient cash and liquid assets to deal with economic downturns? (f) Should the firm arrange more long-term funds? NBER cycle analysis focuses on the US which remains the largest economy in the world. Its economic booms and busts will strongly affect its imports and the global strategies of US companies. Other economies, especially those export-oriented and emerging economies, will suffer from US economic busts. The next cycle peak: 2017-2019 下一個經濟高峰：2017年至2019年 TABLE表3 DURATION OF AN ECONOMIC CYCLE 經濟週期的持續時間 MEDIAN 中位數 UPPER QUARTILE 最高四分之一 MAXIMUM 最高值 MEDIAN 中位數 UPPER QUARTILE 最高四分之一 MAXIMUM 最高值 CYCLE DURATION AFTER 1950 (MONTHS) 1950年後之週期持續時間（月） CYCLE DURATION AFTER 1950 (IN YEAR) 1950年後之週期持續時間（年） Duration, peak to trough 持續時間 (從高峰至低谷) 10.0 14.8 18.0 0.8 1.2 1.5 Duration, trough to peak 持續時間 (從低谷至高峰) 51.5 87.3 120.0 4.3 7.3 10.0 Duration, peak to peak 持續時間 (從高峰至高峰) 65.0 101.3 128.0 5.4 8.4 10.7 Duration, trough to trough 持續時間 (從低谷至低谷) 59.5 97.8 128.0 5.0 8.1 10.7 NB: These statistics are calculated with the data in Table 2 註：以上數據根據表2計算得出。","@ID":38},{"#text":"1 #1  |  2017 THE BUSINESS OF BUSINESS 管理睿智 HONG KONG PROPERTY – TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE? 香港樓市——福兮禍所伏? COUNTERCYCLICAL CORPORATE STRATEGIES 企業逆週期策略 Brian To Global strategist 全球策略家","@ID":1},{"#text":"79 78 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Praveen Choudhary is a Managing Director and heads research for Asian Gaming, Asian Conglomerates and Hong Kong property at Morgan Stanley. He co-led the Hong Kong category to rank #1 in the 2014 and 2015 Institutional Investor All Asia Research Team polls. He has been ranked in the Asian Gaming & Lodging sector each year from 2011 to 2015. He joined the firm in 2002, prior to which he worked at Deutsche Bank’s investment banking division. He has a degree in Electronics Engineering and an MBA from the Indian Institute of Management, Calcutta. Praveen Choudhary現為摩根士丹利執行總裁， 負責亞洲博彩、亞洲集團以及香港房地產方面的 研究。由他所共同領導的香港類別，在2014及 2015年度機構投資者全亞洲研究團隊評選中排名 第一。2011年至2015年期間，他在亞洲博彩及 住宿領域一直名列前茅。Praveen Choudhary曾 於德意志銀行投資銀行部任職，後於2002年加入 摩根士丹利。他擁有印度管理研究所電子工程學 士以及工商管理碩士學位。 Praveen Choudhary Hong Kong property – too good to be true? 香港樓市–福兮禍所伏? By Praveen Choudhary 文︰Praveen Choudhary Morgan Stanley’s Praveen Choudhary examines the current state of the Hong Kong property market and what to expect through 2017. 摩根士丹利執行總裁PraveenChoudhary 詳細剖釋香港樓市概況及2017年的前 景。 About the author 作者簡介","@ID":40},{"#text":"39 38 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Professor Dr Brian To OBE is a global strategist and senior practice professor with over six advanced degrees in business, management, policy, Chinese business and managing change. He consults to several Asian governments and militaries, Fortune 500 corporations and ultrahigh net worth individuals and their familyowned businesses in Asia and North America. Brian presently coaches several country leaders, corporate CEOs and entrepreneurs focused on personal and professional effectiveness and revenue expansion strategies. He can be contacted at bto@post.harvard.edu. 全球策略家及高級實踐型教授Brian To博士，OBE 太平紳士，擁有多於六個工商、管理、政策、中國 商業與變革管理等學科的研究生學位。他為多個亞 洲政府與軍隊、財富美國500強企業，以及極高淨 資產人士與其家族在亞洲、北美擁有的家族企業擔 任顧問。現在，Brian為多位國家領袖、企業行政 總裁與企業家，就提高個人及職業效能，以及制定 提升收益策略的目標提供指導。如欲聯絡Brian To 博士，可電郵至︰bto@post.harvard.edu。 Dr Brian To Brian To 博士 About the author 作者簡介 South China Elitebrings you Dr Brian To’s insights into ethics in the new Chinese economy, how societies innovate and the importance of leadership. Brian To 博士與南華精英分享其對中 國新經濟倫理、社會創新方法，以及 領導管理等領域的精辟見解。 The business of business 管理睿智 By Dr Brian To 文︰Brian To博士","@ID":20},{"#text":"85 84 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Froma demographic perspective, new immigrants, nonlocal students, graduates and employees have been driving the demand for private residential units. In general, the Fed rate and corresponding mortgage rate hike remains one of the key swing factors of the physical market. Hong Kong banks have been reducing mortgage spread from HIBOR (HK Interbank Rate) +170bps in 4Q15 to HIBOR +128bps in March 2017, to offset the 50bps Fed rate hike since December 2016. It is worth noting that room for a mortgage rate spread cut has been reducing – both the speed and magnitude of the spread cuts are declining. Morgan Stanley’s US economists are assuming six more rate hikes in the US by end-2018. If this were to happen and if HIBOR follows a similar trend to the Fed (due to the US peg), the local mortgage rate could double from the current level and could impact not only new buyers but also existing owners. Despite brisk sales at Cullinan West and the Kai Tak area this year, we estimate residential prices will drop by 5% in 2017 driven by higher rates, increasing supply, rising risk of cooling measures and competition for land from Chinese developers, all driving margins lower. These risks can be mitigated by higher global reflation and economic growth. For example, a 5% annual salary growth can offset 50bps of mortgage rate hikes from an affordability ratio point of view. 一般而言，美國聯邦儲備銀行利率和相應的按揭利率 上調，依然是現貨市場波動的關鍵因素之一。為抵消美國 聯邦儲備銀行自2016年12月起利率上調合共50點子，香港銀 行已多次調低按揭利率︰從2015年第4季的香港銀行同業拆 息+170點子，下調至2017年3月的香港銀行同業拆息+128點 子。值得注意的是，調低按揭利率的空間正在收窄，其速度 及幅度均有所放緩。 摩根士丹利的美國經濟師預期，美國將在2018年年底前 6度加息。如果預測正確，香港銀行同業拆息會因聯繫匯率 而跟隨美國聯邦儲備銀行加息，本地按揭利率則會在目前水 平的基礎上翻倍，而影響新買家及現有業主。 儘管匯璽及啟德地區新樓盤交投暢旺，但我們預期2017 年住宅單位價格將下跌5%。高利率、供應增加、遏制樓市過 熱的風險上升，以及中國發展對土地的競爭日益增加等，都 會導致利潤縮窄。 這些風險，可以通過全球通貨再膨脹及經濟增長得以舒 緩。比如說，從負擔能力比率出發，每年5%的薪酬增長，足 以抵消50個點子的按揭利率上調。","@ID":43},{"#text":"91 90 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 有人說，遊艇只讓你快樂兩次——買的那天和賣 的那天。然而，邁進辛普森遊艇香港總部（亞 洲領先的遊艇經銷商之一）的瞬間，我們便意 識到，事實遠非如此。 辛普森遊艇擁有一支充滿熱誠的團隊，對遊艇的各方面 及其寓意的生活方式，都甚為熱衷。 公司的歷史相當有趣且引人注目︰創始人麥克·辛普 森洞察到亞洲的獨特良機後，便於1984年成立公司。 Some say boats only make you happy twice – the day you buy them and the day you sell them. But the moment we step inside Simpson Marine’s offices in Hong Kong – one of Asia’s leading yacht dealers – we realize this is far from the truth. Boasting a team truly motivated by their business, it quickly becomes apparent that Simpson Marine loves everything about boats and the lifestyle that comes with them. The company’s history is as interesting as it is impressive. Founder Mike Simpson started the business in 1984 after recognizing that Asia presented a unique growth opportunity.","@ID":46},{"#text":"99 98 SOUTH CHINA ELITE LAGOON 77","@ID":50},{"#text":"109 108 SOUTH CHINA ELITE There was a time when Lamborghini’s new Hong Kong store sold just six cars a year. Fast forward 20 years and Lamborghini Hong Kong has claimed the title of the world’s best Lamborghini dealer. “When we started in 1992 we just had one model, the Diablo, and globally the company was only producing around 200 cars. In 2015, Lamborghini delivered more than 3,200,” smiles Director Albert Wong. “It’s quite a big jump exponentially. From selling just six cars in the early days, 2015 was a benchmark year for us because we had some new products like the Huracán which was introduced. We delivered more than 100 cars just in Hong Kong alone and luckily enough were the biggest point of sale in the world.” 回顧往昔，林寶堅尼香港經銷店曾經一年只售出 六台車。20年以後，它已經摘得全球最佳林寶 堅尼經銷商的稱號。 公司董事黃卓徽微笑道︰「1992年我們剛起步時，只有 一個車型——Diablo。當時林寶堅尼在全球只生產差不多兩 百台車。2015年，林寶堅尼生產了3,200多台。 「這是相當大的進步。從早期只售出六台開始，2015年 算得上我們標桿性的一年，因為我們有了像Huracán這樣的 新車型，僅在香港我們就售出一百多台，是全球最大的銷售 點。」","@ID":55},{"#text":"77 76 SOUTH CHINA ELITE TABLE表4 THE NEXT ECONOMIC PEAK IN 2017-2019 下一個經濟高峰——2017年至2019年 Last Peak 上一個高峰 PROJECTION WITH 預計 NEXT PEAK (PEAK TO PEAK) 下一個高峰(從高峰至高峰) NEXT PEAK (TROUGH TO PEAK) 下一個高峰(從低谷至高峰) December 2007 2007年12月 MEDIAN (EXPECTED) 中位數（預期） MAY 2013 2013年5月 OCTOBER 2013 2013年10月 Last Trough 上一個低谷 UPPER QUARTILE (LESS EXPECTED) 最高四分之一（預期較低） JUNE 2016 2016年6月 OCTOBER 2016 2016年10月 June 2009 2009年6月 MAXIMUM (CLOSE-TO-UNEXPECTED) 最高（介乎不預期） AUGUST 2018 2018年7月 JUNE 2019 2019年6月 NB:  The last peak and the last trough are confirmed by NBER. 註：對上一個高峰和低谷均為美國全國經濟研究所確認。 在經濟繁榮階段，不少企業憑藉獨特的產品及吸引的營 銷策略得以迅速發展。這樣的繁榮期可延續5年至10年。然 而，不少企業卻沒有為經濟週期的轉折點做好準備。他們在 高峰前過度擴張，故難以在衰退期從客戶處收取債務及向銀 行取得額外貸款。 最後，它們不得不出售業務，甚至破產。準確預測轉 折點看似很困難，但歷史數據就經濟週期的長短提供了不少 線索。企業應在對上一個低谷後4.3年或對上一個高峰後5.4 年，為逆週期策略做好準備。若企業在經濟衰退時擁有充裕 的資金，應在低谷階段購買資產並擴展業務——這一般在對 上一個高峰1.5年後出現。 Summary 總結 Many companies grow fast in economic booms with unique products and attractive marketing strategies. Their booming period may last for five to 10 years. However, some of them don’t prepare sufficiently for turning points in economics cycles.  They over-expand themselves before a peak and therefore find it hard to collect debts from their customers and be provided additional loans from banks in a recession period. Finally, they sell off their business and even go bankrupt. Predicting the exact turning points seems difficult, however statistics from history provide clues on interval estimates of economic cycles. A company should prepare itself for countercyclical corporate strategies 4.3 years after the last trough or 5.4 years after the last peak. If the company is cash-rich in economic downturns, it should acquire assets and expand business at the trough which tends to occur one to 1.5 years after the last peak.","@ID":39},{"#text":"107 106 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Andrew was born in Australia and moved to Hong Kong in 2005 and Macau in 2009, when he founded O MEDIA, which publishes a range of publications including South China Elite. He was the 2014 Macau Person of the Year and regularly appears on television to commentate on Macau. He is a Fellow of the Hong Kong Institute of Directors, a permanent member of the Macau Gaming Management Association, President of the Macau Taxi Passengers Association and a member of the International Federation of Journalists, the Portuguese and English Press Association of Macau and the Poker Tournament Directors Association. He has a BCom and will complete an MSc in Integrated Resort Management at the University of Macau in 2017. 卓奕在澳洲出生，於2005年移居香港。2009年移 居澳門後，他創立了澳傳媒集團，旗下一系列刊 物包括《南華精英》。卓奕是2014年度澳門年度 人物，經常在電視節目上評論澳門時事。此外， 他亦是香港董事學會會員、澳門博彩管理協會會 員、澳門的士乘客協會主席、國際記者聯盟成 員、澳門葡語及英語傳媒協會會員及撲克賽事總 監協會會員。卓奕擁有商學士學位，並將於2017 年完成澳門大學國際綜合度假村管理碩士。 Andrew W Scott 卓奕 Having watched his father set up Lamborghini’s Hong Kong dealership 25 years ago, AlbertWong explainswhy Asia has become an enduring stronghold for the iconic supercar brand. 見證父親在香港代理林寶堅尼25年 的黃卓徽（Albert Wong）向我們 解釋，為何亞洲已成為這個標誌性 超跑品牌的長期基地。 A league of its own 獨佔鰲頭 By Andrew W Scott 文︰卓奕 About the author 作者簡介","@ID":54},{"#text":"61 60 SOUTH CHINA ELITE The core message of the recent Morgan Stanley Blue Paper, “Why We Are Bullish on China” is that Chinese equities can continue to outperform emerging-market equities in the future, as they have done for some time. Cumulative outperformance over the last 15 years for MSCI China versus MSCI EM has been 5,000 basis points, or around 3% per year. China has also outperformed emerging markets over both five and 10 years – and not by small amounts. Total returns have averaged 5% per year in US dollar terms over those periods, and 13% per year over the last 15 years. For us, being overweight on China equities in our recommended allocation to clients investing in the EM space is not unusual. Our structural bullishness in the 10 years I have covered China equities at Morgan Stanley is starkly different from that of the consensus amongst global investors and even EM specialist managers, who have been and remain underweight China. Indeed, 摩根士丹利最近發表題為《我們緣何看好中國》 的藍皮書，其核心信息是中國股票市場將延續 過往的趨勢，在未來持續領先於其他新興國家 的股票市場。過去15年，MSCI中國指數對MSCI新興國家指數 的累積領先幅度達5,000個基點，即每年約3%。 以5年和10年為期，中國股票市場的表現亦明顯比其他新興 國家股票市場優勝。以美元計算，5年和10年期的中國股票 總回報率為平均每年5%，15年期則為平均每年13%。 對我們而言，建議投資新興市場的客戶投放大比例資金 在中國股票，並非新奇事。過去10年，我在摩根士丹利負責 中國股票市場，以結構性角度重點投資中國股票市場。這與 環球投資者甚至新興國家投資專家，仍然對中國股票市場投 資不足的共識思維截然不同。誠然，新興國家投資專家在過 去15年，一直對中國股票市場投資不足。以500個基點為基 準，當前他們對中國股票市場投資之不足，甚至到達歷史低 位。 他們為何對中國股票市場憂心重重？是忽略了我們視為 優勢的因素嗎？我們認為，針對中國股票市場的共識思維， 一直過度偏重於宏觀辯論，尤其是債務可持續性、產能過 剩，以及最近的外匯風險等方面，卻沒有深入分析中國股票 市場優異表現背後的原因。在循環週期中，中國股票市場的 平均股本回報率，明顯比其它新興國家股票市場為高，若以 美元計算，其收益亦較高。我們認為，儘管中國經濟的債務 比重上升，但上述現象的根源，並不在於經濟槓桿作用，而 在於中國股票市場正朝著以消費者、服務以及私營企業為導 向的方向發展，而其發展速度亦高於整體經濟。 2005年，MSCI中國指數總市值中，只有5%來自非國營企 業。至2016年，其比重已激增至近50%。我們在藍皮書中預 計，非國營企業在MSCI中國指數總市值中之比重，在2020年 將上升至70%。阿里巴巴和騰訊等無人不知的非國營企業， 比國營企業有更較高的收入增長及較低的債務，而其表現 在循環週期中亦明顯優於大市，其一原因是他們主要涉及資 訊科技、消費者及醫療保健等領域。正如我們在藍皮書中所 指，這些領域將持續驅動中國晉身高收入國家之列。我們亦 列出了50家在新經濟模式下成為「獨角獸」的中國企業。在 首次公開招股前市值已超越10億美元的中國企業，其數目多 於世界其它地區（不包括美國）之總數。 the latter group is running a near record underweight on China versus the benchmark of 500 basis points currently, and at no point in the last 15 years have EM specialists ever been anything but underweight China. So what is it that the consensus is so worried about and what are they missing which we think is positive? In our view, consensus thinking on China has always been too caught up in the macro debate, particularly in relation to debt sustainability, excess capacity and more recently foreign exchange risk. Consensus has been insufficiently focused on identifying the sources of China’s outperformance, which lie in the market having had a materially higher return on equity (ROE) than the EM average over the cycle, and hence higher earnings growth in US dollar terms. We believe the roots of that phenomenon lie not so much in an economy that is becomingmore leveraged, though it has, but in an equity market that is evolving faster than the overall economy by becoming more consumer- and services-oriented as well as more private sector-driven. In 2005 only 5% of MSCI China’s market capitalization was in non-state-owned sectors. By 2016 it was almost half, and we project in our Blue Paper that non-state-owned firms will be 70% of market cap by 2020. The non-state-owned firms, including household names like Alibaba and Tencent, have higher revenue growth and less leverage than their state-owned peers and have substantially outperformed the market over the cycle as they operate predominantly in IT, Consumer and Healthcare, which are the sectors that we argue in the Blue Paper will continue to drive China’s journey to high-income status. In our Blue Paper we identify 50 Chinese firms in these New Economy sectors that are “unicorns.” That is, they achieved private market valuations of over US$1 billionprior to their initial public offerings. That is more than the number of unicorns in the rest of the world (excluding the US) put together.","@ID":31},{"#text":"87 86 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Lifestyle 生活","@ID":44},{"#text":"5 4 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Cover Story 封面故事 10 Brian To Global Strategist 全球策略家 Contents 目錄 58 Why we are bullish on China 我們緣何看好中國 66 Countercyclical corporate strategies 企業逆週期策略 78 Hong Kong property – too good to be true? 香港樓市——福兮禍所伏? 26 Current trends of private banking and wealth management in Asia 亞洲私人銀行與財富管理之近況及動態 38 The business of business 管理睿智 88 Call of the sea 大海的呼喚 106 A league of its own 獨佔鰲頭 Business 商業 Insights 見解 Lifestyle生活 By Ben Blaschke 文︰本思齊 By Jonathan Garner 文︰Johnathan Garner By Michael C S Wong 文︰王澤森 By Praveen Choudhary 文︰Praveen Choudhary By Raquel Dias 文︰戴樂瑩 By Andrew W Scott 文︰卓奕 By KC Tew 文︰張金全 By Dr Brian To 文︰博士","@ID":3},{"#text":"49 48 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Our role as business educators is to continue our collaboration with our community and society, inspired by innovation and authentic leadership aswe go forth to engage the exciting universe of commerce. 作為商業教育 者，我們的職責 是持續與我們所 屬的社區及社會 合作；憑藉創新 及真正的領導管 理，參與令人振 奮的商業世界。","@ID":25},{"#text":"19 18 SOUTH CHINA ELITE BB: As you said earlier, you spend your life traveling the world. You must be accustomed to traveling these days? BT: Yes and I have several homes but I spend very little time in my own home. For the past 15 years I wouldn’t have spent any more than two weeks a year in my own home. Those of us who travel the world as much as I do tend to think of home as being wherever we are. We think on a global scale. But I can’t complain. I fly everyweek to somewhere, it’s how I get to work and how I get to wherever I need to be for whatever reason. Essentially my work takes me to many countries and many situations that are both friendly and sometimes not so. BB: More and more companies these days are looking to be global companies. How beneficial is it that you yourself operate globally and understand the nature of true globalization? BT: Well that’s correct in as much as I operate in a number of different countries and have clients all around the world. But it’s a privilege really to be able to work with boards, CEOs and Managing Directors that are keen to see growth for their company not just regionally but globally. To assist in formulating innovative strategies and to assist them in the execution of those strategies using my experience is very rewarding when you see it come to fruition. BB: How else are you involved in organizations? BT: I can honesty state that everything I do I love doing,fromboardadvisoryanddevelopmenttoteaching seminars to raising money for various charities – from poverty to women’s causes and building classrooms in rural communities. In every project, program or initiative I have had the opportunity to learn valuable lessons about people, places and problems. 本思齊：正如你剛才所言，你一輩子都穿梭於不同的國 家。經常外出，對你來說應該是司空見慣了吧？ Brian To 博士：我以全球各地為家，卻很少真正留在 自己的家。最近15年間，我每年留在自己家的時間少於兩個 星期。我們這類經常出遊的人一般以身處的地方為家，這可 能是國際視野吧。 但這未嘗不是好事。我每個星期都會乘飛機到工作、會 議或因其它原因而必須要到的地方去。由於工作需要，我要 前往很多國家；情況大多是友好的，但也有不盡人意之時。 本思齊：愈來愈多企業希望成為全球企業。你在全球 各地工作，且了解全球化的真正意義。這對工作有何益處？ Brian To博士：是的，我的足跡遍布多個國家，客戶亦 來自全球各地。有機會與有志在地區乃至全球擴展的企業首 席執行官及執行董事共事，絕對是榮幸。憑藉個人經驗協助 他們制定創新策略、實行方案並取得成果，讓我感到滿足。 BB: Can you provide some insight into how you practically go about changing a company’s direction or adjusting its culture? BT: Traditionally speaking – and it’s the same today – most companies go into what they call an annual planning or strategy session which culminates in beautiful documentation with a beautiful collection of charts and budgets. But the reality when you go into the research is that over 90% of companies fail to meet their objectives annually and predominantly that is due to over-estimation of the market, under-estimation or under-appreciation of the culture they operate in. In some cases it’s just a rehash of the budget and strategy documents of previous years with very minor consideration for inflation, and also the residency of corporate pride and management ego. This is why many fail. 本思齊：除此以外，你還會以何種方式參與組織運 作？ Brian To博士：無論是參與董事局、主持教學研討會、 為慈善組織籌款、扶貧、女性權益或在農村建設教室，我確 實喜歡自己的工作。每一個項目或計劃，對我而言均是學習 人們、地方及問題的寶貴機會。 本思齊：可否與我們分享，你是如何改變公司方針或 企業文化的？ Brian To博士：傳統上——其實今天亦然——多數企業 在年度規劃或策略會議上，都會展出很多精美的文檔、圖表 和預算案等。然而，研究統計指出逾90%的企業均無法實現 年度目標，主要原因是他們高估了市場，卻低估了文化及經 營環境。 有些時候，企業僅重新調整前幾年的預算和策略性文 件而已。決策者當局者迷，卻沒有考慮到通貨膨脹因素。 這正是不少企業變革失敗的原因。","@ID":10},{"#text":"103 102 SOUTH CHINA ELITE SANLORENZO 460 “That is why some of our clients enjoy having their yachts in countries such as Thailand. They know and feel secure in the region and Thailand has a good reputation for being safe and beautiful,” she explains. The process might seem somewhat daunting for a beginner, but Ewa assures us it doesn’t have to be. “You really need to allow people to experience it for themselves,” she continues. “In Europe for example, we are used to seeing marinas and boats, be they big or small, but in Asia it’s still a relatively new reality.” Yachting is about more than just a boat, it’s a lifestyle. Feeling the sunshine on your skin and experiencing the freedom of the sea are just some of the joys of owning a boat. And reading through all of the options Simpson Marine has on offer is certainly enticing – elegant interiors with beautiful finishes, enjoying utmost comfort as you rip through the waves. It is the ultimate personal adventure. 「正因如此，我們的一些客戶選擇在泰國等地擁有遊 艇。他們知道、感到泰國較安全，並有安全、美麗出海勝地 的良好聲譽。」 這個過程對初學者來說，似乎有點令人望而生畏，但 Ewa向我們保證，事情並非一定如此。 她繼續說︰「人們需要親自去體驗。例如在歐洲，我們 習慣看到大大小小的碼頭和遊艇。但在亞洲，它仍是較新的 現象。」 遊艇的意義絕不僅限於船隻本身，它代表一種生活方 式。讓肌膚與陽光親密接觸以及體驗海洋的自由，只是其中 的一些樂趣。翻閱辛普森遊艇的產品目錄，著實讓人怦然心 動——優雅的內飾與悅目的外觀，在乘風破浪時讓您享受最 佳的舒適。這是個人冒險的終極體驗。","@ID":52},{"#text":"15 14 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 本思齊：你在全球頂尖學府任教時，都涉及這些主題 嗎？ Brian To博士：幾十年來，我在全球各地教授工商管 理碩士、高級工商管理碩士、科學碩士、博士、工商管理博 士及管理教育等課程，其中包括的主題有競爭策略、領導管 理、創新及道德倫理等。除了定期教授軍事策略課程外，其 BB: You teach at some of the world’s leading universities. Are these some of the topics you teach? BT: For several decades I have enjoyed teaching graduate programs, namely in MBA, EMBA, MSC, PHD, DBA and executive education programs throughout the world in subjects such as competitive strategy, leadership, innovation and even ethics. With the exception of teaching military strategy courses regularly, most subjects are business and management subjects. I’mblessed to be the recipient of somuchknowledge and experience in every classroom. My students are already accomplished and either corporate leaders, senior government leaders or entrepreneurs whose companies are, for the most part, already publicly listed. My teaching is based on the theory of the subject matter but also the applied practical experience of my work in the context of current case study challenges and developments. BB: Aside from teaching, you have attended some interesting schools as well? BT: I’ve been fortunate to have studied in a number of countries including France, the US and England among others. In every city and country I have been fortunate to learn and appreciate the value of diversity and culture. And yes, in each of those distinguished schools I have had the opportunity to learn from some of the world’s leading scholars and thought leaders. Throughout these most memorable years I am reminded that lifelong learning is a responsibility and a privilege. 它課程大多與商業管理有關。 課室裡的學員都擁有豐富的知識和經驗，令我獲益良 多。我教導的學員多為事業有成者，如企業領導者、政府 高級官員，以及上市公司的企業家等。 在當前個案研究的框架內，我的教學重視理論及個人 實踐經驗、分析各類挑戰及發展。 Harvard University Campus哈佛大學校園 本思齊：除了教學外，你也曾在多國留學吧？ Brian To博士：我曾在美、英、法等國留學，並有幸在 每一個國家和城市學習及欣賞多元性與文化的價值。在多國 著名學府裡，我有機會向頂尖學者及思想領袖學習。 這些難忘的歲月一直提醒我︰終身學習是責任，亦是 榮幸。","@ID":8},{"#text":"67 66 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Dr Michael C S Wong is an Associate Professor of Finance at City University of Hong Kong. He advises many Asian banks on risk management, reviews their risk models and serves as an expert witness on litigations relating to complex financial transactions. Dr Wong graduated from Essex, CambridgeandtheChineseUniversityofHongKong, with executive training at UC Berkeley and MIT.  He is an appointed member of the Market Misconduct Tribunal in Hong Kong and HKSAR Government’s Future Task Force of the Insurance Industry. 王澤森博士現為香港城市大學經濟及金融系副教 授，經常向亞洲地區銀行就風險管理提供建議並 審視其風險模式，亦在複雜金融交易相關的訴訟 擔任專家證人。王澤森博士畢業於埃塞克斯大 學、劍橋大學及香港中文大學，並於加州大學伯 克利分校和麻省理工學院接受主管培訓。他亦是 市場失當行為審裁處委員，以及香港特區政府保 險業未來發展工作小組成員。 Michael C S Wong 王澤森 City University of Hong Kong香港城市大學 Countercyclical corporate strategies 企業逆週期策略 By Michael C S Wong 文︰王澤森 Dr Michael Wong delves into the duration of economic cycles and how corporations can better prepare for upcoming peaks and troughs. 王澤森博士深入分析經濟週期，以及企業 該如何為未來的高峰和低谷做好準備。 About the author 作者簡介","@ID":34},{"#text":"95 94 SOUTH CHINA ELITE BENETEAU OCEANIS YACHT","@ID":48},{"#text":"35 34 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Since competition for their funds is extremely keen, all players nowadays have to change and develop business strategies that fit their own strengths or unique characteristics. For example, the mega banks like UBS and JP Morgan have the ability to provide financial services to the ultra-HNWIs (UHNWIs) who have assets in excess of US$50 million, with some of them in the hundreds of millions level. These UHNWIs usually have their own professional financial advisors and demand impeccable services which cannot be offered by the smaller banks or IFAs.  Their investment requirements usually extend to investment banking services such as overseas acquisitions, issuance of corporate bonds, financial advisory services and international business purchases such as commercial real estates. The big global banks have all the supporting capabilities. The fee-income generating potential is extensive. The boutique or pure-play banks come mainly from Switzerland and Liechtenstein. Their strengths are inherent in the ability to provide personalized services with unique investment opportunities in Switzerland and Europe, in conjunction with family trusts and foundations.  They are usually strong in discretionary portfolio management. Their market segments encompass HNWIs who demand exclusivity. In Asia, the two locomotives of the growth of individual wealth are China and India. Overall, the growth in Asia has already surpassed Europe and is catching up with North America. Singapore has the advantage for Indian sub-continent clients, viz India, Pakistan, Bangladesh and Sri Lanka.  Hong Kong dominates over the Greater China region, which includes mainland China, Hong Kong and Taiwan. According to Frank Knight’s 2016 Wealth Report, there are now more than 13 million millionaires across the globe, up from 8.7 million in 2005. These HNWIs own from one million to billions of dollars of assets, amounting to US$66 trillion, which is more than the value of all global equities. The US is still the leader, with 1.25 million millionaires, followed by 490,500 in China, 253,500 in the UK and 247,800 in India. 高淨值人士財富管理業務競爭非常激烈，現今所有參 與者均須改變及發展出符合既有優勢或特性的商業策略。例 如，瑞士銀行及摩根大通等巨型銀行，均有能力為超高淨值 人士提供金融服務；所謂的超高淨值人士，即擁有5千萬美 元或以上資產的人士，有的甚至擁有數億美元之多。超高淨 值人士一般擁有自己的專業財務顧問，並要求極為優質的頂 級服務。規模較小的銀行及獨立財務顧問等，一般難以提供 此類服務。超高淨值人士的投資要求，一般牽涉及到海外收 購、發行企業債券及財務諮詢等投資銀行服務，以及商用物 業等國際業務採購。跨國大型銀行有能力提供全面的支援， 而其費用收入的潛力亦甚大。 小型精品或單一業務銀行，大多來自瑞士和列支敦士 登。其優勢在於提供個人化服務、在瑞士和歐洲各地尋找獨 特的投資機會，並提供家族信託及基金服務。它們大多擅於 全權委託投資組合管理，客戶主要是要求高級私人服務的超 高淨值人士。 中國和印度是亞洲個人財富增長的兩大火車頭。總體而 言，亞洲的增長已經超越歐洲，並正在趕上北美。新加坡的 優勢，在於擁有印度、巴基斯坦、孟加拉和斯里蘭卡等國的 印度次大陸客戶。香港則在大中華地區（包括中國、香港和 台灣）佔主導地位。 根據2016年度萊坊財富報告，全球現有1,300萬位百萬 富翁，高於2005年時的870萬。這些高淨值人士擁有的資 產，由1百萬美元至數十億美元不等，總值約66萬億美元， 超過全球所有股票的總值。美國依然排名榜首，擁有125 萬位百萬富翁，緊隨其後的是中國（490,500位）、英國 （253,500位）及印度（247,800位）。","@ID":18},{"#text":"47 46 SOUTH CHINA ELITE For over 50 years of academic programs in all classes of society – particularly in Hong Kong and Singapore, among others – medicine, engineering and professional disciplines like law and business have been the most attractive programs for parents to encourage their children to enrol in. However, while all of these programs have their merits and benefits, it is my faithful reminder that without the study of human interaction, behaviour and communications, the students would find themselves irrelevant in a fastchanging world and would be restricted in enabling their professional effectiveness in a given situation. It is clearly evidenced when new graduates are undergoing job interviews; many are unable to piece together a complete and comprehensible sentence. In fact, a considerable number of graduates utterly lack social skills and even a basic understanding of human behaviour. The evident uneasiness in interviews and group settings of even those armed with five years of work experience is even more troubling in management education. What are the caveats to further management education? Hypercompetitive competition and economic turbulence never before seen at this rate have caused all of us to be focused around growth and change in the midst of increasing shrinking profitability. In this era of rapid innovation, we are charged with managing value whilst being reshaped by globalization and technology, which will reshape our future. As we continue to devote ourselves to serving the global community through education in both management andbusiness programs throughDBA, PhD, EMBA and MBA and other offerings, we must recognize that our study together is really a commitment and conviction that good leadership and management can indeed make countries, companies and societies more capable and more vibrant. Whilst a growth in enrolment in management educationhasbeennoticedinrecentyears,onecuriously observes that motivation for candidacy varies. Some, for example, would treasure the opportunity to have advanced one’s standing in a business career, while others are looking to fill space on an office wall or a conversation piece on the golf course. Despite varying motivation, it’s fair to acknowledge that the opportunity is really about advancing one’s “intellectual ambition” and advancing our organization’s inclusion in the global marketplace. Our role as business educators is to continue our collaboration with our community and society, inspired by innovation and authentic leadership as we go forth to engage the exciting universe of commerce. 如果每隔20年才參加一次領導管理教育，其成效是有 限的。研究領導管理時，不應只限於討論最新的潮流和模 式，而是必須在堅實的行為科學基礎上，深入剖析領導管 理。現時，得以在企業內晉升成高層的管理者，依賴的往 往不是創新、激勵及技巧，而是政治頭腦及手段。回到你 剛才提出的問題：最近幾年間，這對管理教育構成了極大 的影響，針對此議題而發表的理論，總數更超越50,000之 多。在競爭愈加激烈及經濟環境持續改變的今天，教育是 重中之重。再者，在混亂與運作之間取得平衡，需要的正 是領導管理。 過去50多年間，香港及新加坡的父母一直鼓勵子女攻 讀醫學、工程、法律及商業等專業學科。其實，任何學科 均有其優點和好處，但我的忠告是，如果缺乏人際互動、 行為及溝通等方面的學習，畢業生將難以融入這個瞬息萬 變的世界，其專業效能亦將大受限制。這在畢業生進行面 試時已可見一斑：很多人甚至難以組織出完整有序的句 子。事實上，不少人完全缺乏社交技巧，以及對人類行為 的基本認知。擁有五年工作經驗的人，在面試及團體活動 中仍然顯得不安。這令人對管理教育感到憂心忡忡。 推進管理教育時，應注意哪些事項？ 前所未有的激烈競爭及經濟動盪，令盈利能力不斷 萎縮，使我們更為關注增長及變化。在這個快速創新的時 代，我們負責管理價值的同時，全球化及科技亦重塑我們 及未來。 我們致力通過工商管理博士、博士、高級工商管理碩 士、工商管理碩士及其它課程推動商業管理教育，以為國 際社會服務。與此同時，我們必須認識到，共同努力其實 是一個承諾和信念——良好的領導管理能確實賦予國家、 企業及社會更大的能力和活力。 儘管近年入讀管理教育課程的學員人數有所增加，但 我們注意到，報讀者背後的動機不盡相同。某些人希望籍 此在職場上進步，亦有些人希望能夠在辦公室內或高爾夫 球場上參與對話。動機雖然不盡相同，但學員均視課程為 增進個人知識，並讓企業融入全球市場的機會。 身為商業教育者，我們的職責是繼續與我們所屬的社 區及社會合作，憑藉創新及真正的領導管理，參與令人振 奮的商業世界。","@ID":24},{"#text":"41 40 SOUTH CHINA ELITE How would you characterize the Chinese economy? As it is unfolding, clearly the economy is in a major transition. With double digit growth for decades, the economy is moving from a hyper emerging economy to strategic positioning in the global economic landscapewith a comfortable GDP somewhere within the 6% to 8% range. Further, in order to sustain global growth, the Central Government saw a compelling necessity to engage in a disciplined effort to align the leadership and management of both SOE’s and corporate China through principled leadership and ethical management practices. Understandably, this has caused the highlighting of gaps in management processes, facilitation methods and leadership practices. Today, the consequences of significant corruption are challenging where past practices can no longer be the modus operandi for leaders in both facilitating business growth and expansion. The new generation has to adopt principled and ethical leadership practices. And it has to be deeply rooted in one’s consciousness because under the present leadership of China, this is obviously not an invitation but more of a demand. 你認為中國經濟有何特徵？ 中國經濟顯然處於關鍵的轉型階段。經歷了數十年的每 年雙位數增長後，中國經濟從新興經濟體系高速增長階段， 至今在全球經濟版圖中立下一個策略性定位，而國內生產總 值則維持在每年6%至8%的健康水平。 與此同時，為了維持全球經濟增長，中央政府明白必須 通過合乎道德倫理的領導管理方法及有紀律的方式，整治國 有企業與中國企業的管理措施。 這樣一來，中國在管理過程、促進發展和領導管理方式 的弊端，便開始為人們所注視。現在，我們明白到貪污問題 的嚴重後果，領導者已不能再以舊有作風和慣常做法去推動 經濟發展。新一代領導者須採取合乎道德倫理的領導管理方 式。這需要由心而發地進行，因為在中國當前的領導管理生 態中，革新顯然不是選擇，而是必須的。 On China’s economy and its future 論中國經濟及其前景 What can you say about China and its environment? There are possibly billions of opinions on how China is doing with the economy and its environmental agenda, from human rights to labour unrest. It has been the whipping boy of foreign leaders in their campaign platforms this year but despite perpetual negative assaults, China’s economy has still performed well compared to other leading nations who’s GDP has struggled to reach even 3%. And as chill winds blow across all of Asia, these challenges for China are not trivial but mammoth in scope and consequence. Whilst many who travel to Beijing and Shanghai realize and have become conditioned to the perpetual smog, pollution and dark skies above, a government urbanization plan unfolded earlier this year and this strategy aims to ultimately increase the residential and commercial density, reducing commuting distance and accommodating the endless millions of people moving to the cities each year. It’s a race against time in order to reduce pollution and prepare to accommodate an expected 100 million-plus peoplemoving into the country’s cities by 2020. The greatest migration on planet earthwill undoubtedly continue. 你如何看待中國及其環境問題？ 針對中國經濟、環境、人權及勞工紛爭等議題而發表的 意見，數目猶如恒河沙數。不少國家的政府正值大選年，無 不就上述議題對中國大肆抨擊。儘管批評聲音不斷，但是與 其它先進國家勉強取得的3%經濟增長率相比，中國經濟依然 表現良好。寒風席捲亞洲各地時，這些挑戰對中國絕非無足 輕重，而是會帶來引致嚴重後果的深廣影響。 當不少前往北京及上海的旅客，對城市上空連年不斷的 霧霾及污染習以為常之時，政府就於本年初推出新的城市化 計劃，力圖提高住宅及商業密度、減低兩者距離，並為每年 數以百萬從鄉村移居城市的人口提供安身之所。 減低污染、為2020年前從鄉村移居城市的1億人口提供 安身之所，已刻不容緩。這地球上規模最大的移民潮，無疑 會繼續下去。","@ID":21},{"#text":"55 54 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 我們能促進領導管理及勇氣嗎？ 所有首席執行官、執行董事及經理等，均直覺地、本能 地知道，無論企業的規模及風格為何，都有責任和義務推動 企業內的領導管理及勇氣。在這個競爭異常激烈的變革時期 出現的挑戰，可能是我們沒有準備好面對的，又或是未有接 受過訓練去應對的。領導管理需要過人的勇氣、人際溝通技 巧，以及對員工表現的熱誠、關注與包容。 儘管存在挑戰，有時候它們會與個人偏好和情況背道而 馳。然而，具備前瞻性並激勵他人更積極參與，仍然是我們 的主要機會之一。通過了解他人和自己，我們就能以合乎道 德倫理且高效的方式，為競爭做好準備。 做人行事要勇敢，還要謹記——待人以禮，總比咄咄逼 人為妙。 Can we advance leadership and courage? All CEOs, Managing Directors and Managers intuitively and instinctively know that we have a duty and responsibility to advocate leadership and courage throughout the organization regardless of size and shape. In this period of hypercompetitive change, many challenges are presented that we may not be particularly prepared for or were not trained for. Leadership requires courage and superior interpersonal skills as well as a passion for human performance and a focus on inclusion. At times this may seem at odds with individual preference and circumstances, albeit sometimes challenging. But having a vision of what should be done and inspiring others to greater involvement and participation remains one of our greatest opportunities. Clearly by understanding others and ourselves better, we can best prepare for competition and change ethically and productively. Be courageous and remember, it’s better to always be kind than always be right.","@ID":28},{"#text":"11 10 SOUTH CHINA ELITE Having long been an avid sports fan, Ben put his passion to good use – embarking on a decade-long career as a sports journalist for leading Australian newspapers and sports magazines before joining O MEDIA in Macau in 2013. Aside from covering some of the world’s biggest sporting events, including the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing, Ben has long had an interest in big industry which has led him to cover the gaming sector and beyond in Macau and Hong Kong. In his spare time Ben loves good food, fine wine and a touch of pampering! 熱衷體育活動的本思齊，曾於澳洲各頂尖報章及 雜誌擔任體育記者10年，及後於2013年加入澳傳 媒集團。除了報導如2008年北京奧運會等國際大 型體育活動外，本思齊亦對企業深感興趣，亦因 而開始在港澳地區報導博彩等多個行業。業餘時 間的本思齊，可是美食家、葡萄酒愛好者和懂得 享受生活的人！ South China Elite sat down with jet-setting global strategist Dr Brian To OBE in order to discuss his unique career advising some of the world’s most significant business and political leaders. 足跡遍布全球各地的策略家 Brian To 博士, OBE太平紳士撥冗接受南華精英 訪談，細說其為世界頂尖企業及政治 領袖擔任顧問的事業歷程。 Brian To Global strategist 全球策略家 By Ben Blaschke 文︰本思齐 Ben Blaschke 本思齊 About the author 作者簡介","@ID":6},{"#text":"7 6 SOUTH CHINA ELITE 集團首席執行官 卓奕 幕僚長 麥致遠 行政總監 鄭詩韻 行政經理 MARIA MADDEN 行政助理 吳雪怡 Group CEO ANDREW W SCOTT Chief of Staff MICHAEL MARIAKIS Director and Administrator CYNTHIA CHEANG Admin Manager MARIA MADDEN Admin Assistant SUIE NG ON THE COVER Dr Brian To Brian To博士 Photography 攝影： Gábor Sebestyén Location: London, UK 地點：英國倫敦 #1  | 2017 www.southchinaelite.com 營業及市場高級副總裁 張詩敏 市場副總裁 陳紹文 銷售及業務發展副總監 何敬斌 客戶關係經理 洪毅瑩 香港區銷售 黃湘湘 SVP Sales and Marketing SEMON CHEUNG VP Marketing DERRICK TRAN Associate Director Sales and Business Development JADESON HO Client Relationship Manager DAPHNE HONG HK Sales ANGEL WONG 新聞稿發送至 廣告垂詢 發行查詢 訂閱查詢 IT查詢 一般查詢 Send press releases to For advertising enquiries For distribution enquiries For subscription enquiries For IT enquiries For general enquiries editorial@southchinaelite.com ads@southchinaelite.com distribution@southchinaelite.com subs@southchinaelite.com it@southchinaelite.com info@southchinaelite.com CONTACT US 聯絡我們 Corporate行政 Distribution發行 Sales & Marketing銷售及市場 Distribution Supervisor EMILY VONG Distribution Officers ANSON IP PENG CHEANG MAK MAN WAH HOI HOU WAI 發行部主任 王禧婷 發行部專員 葉少揚 鄭國平 麥敏華 許浩偉 Published by South China Elite Limited Golden Dragon Centre 105 Avenida Xian Xing Hai, 10L, Macau Printed by Paramount Printing Company Limited 3 Chun Kwong Street Tseung Kwan O, Hong Kong 由品亞有限公司出版 澳門冼星海大馬路105號 金龍中心10 樓 L 室 由百樂門印刷有限公司印製 香港新界將軍澳將軍澳工業邨 駿光街三號","@ID":4},{"#text":"17 16 SOUTH CHINA ELITE BB: Is that why you continue to study to this day? BT: Yes because the more you know, or think you know, the more you realize that you don’t actually know much at all. It’s this whole notion of enquiry. When you’re teaching Nobel Prize winners and national scholars and the best brains in the world at the best schools, that’s a pretty good way to realize how much more there is to know. And that’s not false modesty, it’s true – I still go to some classes and have no clue what they are talking about! So that is reinforcement of what you don’t know. When you have a modest amount of diverse clients who are paying you good money, you owe it to them to not only be able to keep up but to be a valuable contributor to your clients. Think about it in the context of medicine. Do you really want your brain operation from someone that earned their degree many, many years ago and has done a couple of online courses since or do you want to know that your surgeon is really employing state of the art technology? Of course you want the very best! If you have a patient on the table and you must execute a corporate operation, who do you really want to operate on you? The only way is to not only study regularly and with a passion but also to practice the very latest theories and methods. 本思齊：這是你至今一直學習的原因嗎？ Brian To博士：是的。當一個人知道得愈多，或認為自己 知道得愈多時，才發覺自己知道的其實很少。這就是研究探索 的核心。 在著名學府教導諾貝爾獎得主、各國頂級學者及全球精 英時，讓人明白到自己要學習的還有很多！這不是客氣話， 而是真確的——有時候，我出席某些課程時，還真的不知道 他們在談甚麼！ 這有助於找出知識的盲點。當你有一定數量、來自不 同背景的客戶向你支付學費時，你的責任就不限於與他們接 軌，而更需要為他們提供寶貴意見。 以醫學為例，如果要接受腦部手術，你會選擇一位畢業 多年，後來完成了幾個遙距課程的醫生，還是一個真正採用 最先進技術的醫生？選擇最好的，是人之常情。 如果躺在手術床上的病人是一家企業，你希望誰來操 刀？唯一的選擇，就是專心致志地學習，並應用最新的理論 及方法。 My teaching is based on the theory of the subjectmatter but also the applied practical experience of mywork. 我的教學重視理 論及應用本人工 作的實際經驗。","@ID":9}]}}